{"id": "6834", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6834", "title": "Langer Briser", "text": "Langer Briser is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Arbalest\"&gt;Arbalest&lt;/a&gt; from \"\".\nIts high added &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Damage\"&gt;Lightning Damage&lt;/a&gt; combined with its chance of inflicting &lt;a href=\"Open%20Wounds\"&gt;Open Wounds&lt;/a&gt; is extremely useful, and its knockback certainly keeps enemies at bay. Some character &lt;a href=\"classes\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; can use it more effectively than others however, as &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Speed\"&gt;Attack Speed&lt;/a&gt;s vary from class to class. It is also one of the only &lt;a href=\"bows\"&gt;bows&lt;/a&gt; that have &lt;a href=\"magic%20find\"&gt;magic find&lt;/a&gt; as an attribute.\nStats.\nTwo-Hand Damage: (37-42) To (82-111)\nRequired Level: 32\nRequired Strength: 52\nRequired Dexterity: 61\nCrossbow Class -\nTrivia.\nIt's name might be a reference to a videogame series &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Langrisser\"&gt;Langrisser&lt;/a&gt; The game centering around the legendary sword called the Langrisser, A German for \"Lung Ripper\". The Open Wound chance modifier seems to directly allude to this namesake."}
