{"id": "24691", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24691", "title": "Laws of Hope", "text": "Laws of Hope is a Law skill, resembling the &lt;a href=\"Prayer\"&gt;Prayer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Aura\"&gt;Aura&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Law has a 60 yard radius. Only one Law skill per Crusader can be learned, but different Laws and different rune effects from several Crusaders stack. The amounts of damage &lt;a href=\"absorb\"&gt;absorb&lt;/a&gt;ed and &lt;a href=\"Life%20per%20second\"&gt;Life per second&lt;/a&gt; gained scale with level, up to 124128 damage and 10728 Life per second at level 70. Basic effect of the same Laws from different Crusaders does not stack.\nAllies include &lt;a href=\"follower\"&gt;follower&lt;/a&gt;s, players, minions and &lt;a href=\"pets\"&gt;pets&lt;/a&gt;.\nDevelopment.\nThe Stop Time skill rune was removed in patch 2.2.0, and replaced with Promise of Faith.\nStop Time: Empowering the Law also causes all health loss and regeneration to pause for 3 seconds. While this effect lasts, the Crusader and affected allies will receive no healing, but will also reduce any unsaved damage taken to 0. This does not count as making them immune to damage (and therefore secondary effects of enemy attacks can still trigger properly)."}
