{"id": "11438", "revid": "3459498", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11438", "title": "Leech-life Ball", "text": "The Life-Leech Ball or Life Steal Missile is the signature move of the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt looks and behaves similar to a , and since Vampires also cast Fireballs, it is easy to not notice the difference. The skills can be most easily identified by the projectile. The Life Steal Missile resembles a burning skull and causes the red life-stealing vortex to appear over the Vampire on a successful hit, whereas the Fireball is a sphere of fire and does not absorb life.\nMechanics.\nThe caster throws a fireball-like missile towards the player or his minion/hireling that drains some Life and replenishes the caster's, as if a player had used a Life-stealing weapon. This skill can be considered a reference towards the mythical Vampires that consumed their victims blood to survive, except that they take it by a spell and not by biting their victim."}
{"id": "31899", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31899", "title": "Leech (Demon Hunter)", "text": "Leech is a passive skill, unlocked at Level 60. It was added in patch 2.3.0.\nIn-game.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Life%20per%20Hit\"&gt;Life per Hit&lt;/a&gt; amount granted scales with level, up to 18507 at level 70. "}
{"id": "35184", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35184", "title": "Leech (Necromancer)", "text": "Leech is a Curse skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". Its role is similar to the classic &lt;a href=\"Life%20Tap\"&gt;Life Tap&lt;/a&gt;: to grant the Necromancer &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; from enemies upon damaging attacks.\nIn-game.\nWhen activated, this skill curses the ground within the targeted area for 1 second. Any enemy touched by it will be cursed for 30 seconds.\nAn enemy that is cursed with Leech will heal a player and their minions when the player attacks it.\nLeech functions differently to &lt;a href=\"Life%20on%20Hit\"&gt;Life on Hit&lt;/a&gt;. Instead of healing the player for 2% of their maximum health with each attack/cast, the amount of healing received scales with the &lt;a href=\"Proc%20Coefficient\"&gt;Proc Coefficient&lt;/a&gt; of each skill and the number of cursed enemies hit.\nHealing from Leech is not shared between players. Each player heals themselves from their own attacks made against a cursed enemy: however, all players, of any class, can gain healing from enemies the Necromancer curses with Leech.\nUnlike \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" Curses, in \"Diablo III\" multiple curses can afflict the same target.\nDevelopment.\nThe reason that there is no &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt; on Leech is that the lack of a cooldown is justified from a cost/benefit perspective."}
{"id": "35183", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35183", "title": "Leech (magic suffix)", "text": "Leech is a &lt;a href=\"suffix\"&gt;suffix&lt;/a&gt; that can appear on &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;. It provides a small &lt;a href=\"Life%20Steal\"&gt;Life Steal&lt;/a&gt; bonus.\nIt can start spawning on items at &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; 6, but will not be able to spawn on all items until level 34. Some items also are not able to acquire full effect.\nThe steal comes from how much damage you do to the monster. So 5% Life Stolen will return 5% of the damage you do to a monster. Life steal only works on melee and physical ranged attacks.\nSome monsters and objects, like &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Tower\"&gt;Fire Tower&lt;/a&gt;s, will not give life when attacked.\nStats.\n\"Can appear on:\" &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic Items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;\n\"Is available on:\" &lt;a href=\"Weapons\"&gt;Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Circlets\"&gt;Circlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rings\"&gt;Rings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Amulets\"&gt;Amulets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gloves\"&gt;Gloves&lt;/a&gt;"}
