{"id": "23087", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23087", "title": "Legacy of Nightmares", "text": "Legacy of Nightmares (named Legacy of Wicked Dreams pre-\"&lt;a href=\"Reaper%20of%20Souls\"&gt;Reaper of Souls&lt;/a&gt;\") is a minor\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". Both pieces require a character level of 60 to drop.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Season\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt; 17, all characters have this bonus for free, as long as they have no others (does not stack with the LoN itself).\nIn patch 2.6.6, a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Gem\"&gt;Legendary Gem&lt;/a&gt; with a similar bonus has been added: &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20Dreams\"&gt;Legacy of Dreams&lt;/a&gt;.\nPieces.\nSet Bonus (2 items):\nDevelopment.\nOriginal set bonus of this set (pre-2.4) was significantly different:\nThe last bonus had a small (roughly 10%) chance to trigger, and a 15 seconds duration with no internal &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt;. There was no cap of how many Skeletons can be summoned at a time.\nAt early stages of 2.4 testing, the bonus for an Ancient item was as high as 800% damage."}
