{"id": "1994", "revid": "5212732", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1994", "title": "Lester", "text": "Lester the Farmer was an inhabitant of &lt;a href=\"Tristram\"&gt;Tristram&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Darkening%20of%20Tristram\"&gt;Darkening of Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, Lester found\u00a0something swelling out of the ground, preventing him from getting to his crops and bales of hay. After seeing &lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;Adria&lt;/a&gt;, she gave him a &lt;a href=\"rune%20bomb\"&gt;rune bomb&lt;/a&gt;, saying it would remove the thing from the field. He asked a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20I\"&gt;hero&lt;/a&gt; to do it for him, as he had to watch his &lt;a href=\"cow\"&gt;cow&lt;/a&gt;s. The hero obliged and detonated the bomb, revealing the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Festering%20Nest\"&gt;Festering Nest&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nLester is exclusive to \"\". He can be seen talking to his cows, and the other townsfolk think he has gone mad, but feel sorry for him because he lost everything. He initiates the &lt;a href=\"Farmer%27s%20Orchard%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Farmer's Orchard&lt;/a&gt; quest. Unlike the classic \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\" NPCs, Lester does not have any gossip and can not be asked about quests. After the hero opens up the Hive with the rune bomb, the next time he/she returns to Tristram from underground, Lester will have departed.\nIn beta versions of \"Hellfire\", Lester used to have a bigger role as a comic relief character. Using the &lt;a href=\"Command.txt%20exploit\"&gt;Command.txt exploit&lt;/a&gt; replaces Lester with the &lt;a href=\"Complete%20Nut\"&gt;Complete Nut&lt;/a&gt; (Lester in disguise), allowing players to take the &lt;a href=\"Jersey%27s%20Jersey\"&gt;Jersey's Jersey&lt;/a&gt; quest. It's possible that, originally, Lester would remain on the map as Complete Nut rather than disappear after his quests."}
{"id": "4812", "revid": "865253", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4812", "title": "Lester the Farmer", "text": ""}
