{"id": "11901", "revid": "53819335", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11901", "title": "Level 4 (Diablo I)", "text": "Level 4 is the fourth and the last Cathedral-style level in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\". The player(s) reaches Level 4 after descending a stairway in &lt;a href=\"Level%203%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 3&lt;/a&gt;. Somewhere in Level 4 there is a stairway to &lt;a href=\"Level%205%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 5&lt;/a&gt; (not shown on the map if tavern sign was stolen, see &lt;a href=\"Ogden%27s%20Sign%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Ogden's Sign&lt;/a&gt;).\nIt holds a glimpse of which monsters may cross the player(s) way in \"the Catacombs\" (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Clan\"&gt;Flesh Clan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gloom\"&gt;Gloom&lt;/a&gt;), and the first demon types apart of &lt;a href=\"Hidden\"&gt;Hidden&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Clan\"&gt;Flesh Clan&lt;/a&gt;).\nQuests.\nIf available, the following quests can be done or initiated in Level 4:\nLevel Bestiary.\nThe following monsters can be found in Level 4:"}
{"id": "12857", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12857", "title": "Level 5 (Diablo I)", "text": "Level 5 is the first Catacombs-style level in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\". The player(s) reaches Level 5 from a stairway in &lt;a href=\"Level%204%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 4&lt;/a&gt;. Somewhere in Level 5, there is a stairway to &lt;a href=\"Level%206%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 6&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpon entering Level 5, the character says, \"The smell of death surrounds me\".\nIt features much less open space, a somewhat maze like layout and a much more gloomy atmosphere.\n&lt;a href=\"Overlord\"&gt;Overlords&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Winged%20Demon\"&gt;Winged Demons&lt;/a&gt; will start appearing from this level on, so the player(s) should be on guard when traversing the hallways.\nQuests.\nIf available, the following quests can be done or initiated in Level 5:\nLevel Beastiary.\nThe following monsters can be found in Level 5:"}
{"id": "12859", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12859", "title": "Level 6 (Diablo I)", "text": "Level 6 is the second Catacombs-style level in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\". The player(s) reaches Level 6 after from a stairway in &lt;a href=\"Level%205%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 5&lt;/a&gt;. Somewhere in Level 6 there is a stairway to &lt;a href=\"Level%207%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 7&lt;/a&gt;.\nLike all catacomb levels, it's dark, cramped, and somewhat confusing to the inexperienced. This level is populated mostly by demons.\nQuests.\nThis level features the generated &lt;a href=\"Chamber%20of%20Bone\"&gt;Chamber of Bone quest&lt;/a&gt;, which awards the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Guardian spell&lt;/a&gt;, or raises it by one level if the character already possesses it, along with a few magical items in chests. Also, lots of undead are to be found, as expected; &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Horror Captains&lt;/a&gt;, to be exact. It takes place in a split level; unlocked when &lt;a href=\"Mythical%20Book\"&gt;Mythical Book&lt;/a&gt; on the same level is read.\nIt's good to know that opening the middle door of the Chamber of Bone usually yields in an entire room filled to the absolute brim with Horror Captains. Past that are some &lt;a href=\"Horned%20Demon\"&gt;Horned Demon&lt;/a&gt;s ready to charge you in a rather open area, guarding a... well, guardian &lt;a href=\"Spellbook\"&gt;spellbook&lt;/a&gt;. It should be read while the enemies are distracted. Reading it automatically summons a Hydra to breath &lt;a href=\"Firebolt\"&gt;Firebolt&lt;/a&gt; at the players foes, but only for a limited time.\nLevel Beastiary.\nThe following monsters can be found in Level 6:"}
{"id": "11994", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11994", "title": "Level 7 (Diablo I)", "text": "Level 7 is the third Catacombs-style level in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\". The player(s) reaches Level 7 from walking a stairway in &lt;a href=\"Level%206%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 6&lt;/a&gt;. Somewhere in Level 7 there is a stairway to &lt;a href=\"Level%208%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 8&lt;/a&gt;. In this level all &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; disappear.\nQuests.\nIf available, the following quest can be done or initiated in Level 7:\nLevel Beastiary.\nThe following monsters can be found in Level 7:"}
{"id": "9965", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9965", "title": "Level 8 (Diablo I)", "text": "Level 8 is the fourth and the last of the Catacombs-style level in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\". The player(s) reaches Level 8 after from a stairway in &lt;a href=\"Level%207%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 7&lt;/a&gt;. Somewhere in Level 8 there is a stairway to &lt;a href=\"Level%209%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 9&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuests.\nIf available, a quest called &lt;a href=\"Zhar%20the%20Mad%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Zhar the Mad&lt;/a&gt; can be obtained by talking to a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Counselor\"&gt;Counselor&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; called...\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Zhar%20the%20Mad\"&gt;Zhar the Mad&lt;/a&gt;\". Speaking to him will activate his namesake quest.\nHe will wonder why the player is there and says that all these interruptions are enough to make one insane (and then laughs madly). He will then give the player a spell book and asks to be left alone to do his work in peace. If the player then tries to grab a spell book from his bookcase, he will be infuriated and he will then attack the player.\nLevel Beastiary.\nThe following monsters can be found in Level 8:"}
{"id": "11909", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11909", "title": "Level 9 (Diablo I)", "text": "Level 9 is the first Caves-style level in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\". \nThe player(s) reaches Level 9 from a stairway in &lt;a href=\"Level%208%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 8&lt;/a&gt;. Somewhere in Level 9 there is a stairway to &lt;a href=\"Level%2010%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 10&lt;/a&gt;. This level has all &lt;a href=\"Magma%20Demon\"&gt;Magma Demon&lt;/a&gt; types in it.\nUpon entering Level 9, the character mentions, \"It's hot down here\".\nQuests.\nIf available, the following quest can be done or initiated in Level 9:\nLevel Beastiary.\nThe following monsters can be found in Level 9:"}
