{"id": "41568", "revid": "29014615", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41568", "title": "Liene", "text": "Liene is a &lt;a href=\"Rogue\"&gt;Rogue&lt;/a&gt; and member of the &lt;a href=\"Sisterhood%20of%20the%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Sisterhood of the Sightless Eye&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, Liene was in the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt; with numerous other Sisters, in their actions against the &lt;a href=\"Bloodsworn\"&gt;Bloodsworn&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Kashya\"&gt;Kashya&lt;/a&gt; ordered her to wait for a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero/group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; that she would ally with, and she could guide them to the Sisterhood's camp. She came under attack by &lt;a href=\"Fallen\"&gt;Fallen&lt;/a&gt;, however, but was saved by the hero(es) she'd been instructed to wait for. They fended the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s off, and Liene directed them to the camp, asking them to kill any Fallen they found along the way.\nLater, Liene and a band of Rogues were ambushed by the Bloodsworn in the &lt;a href=\"Sanguine%20Ruins\"&gt;Sanguine Ruins&lt;/a&gt;. Liene and a number of Rogues were captured and taken to the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Rose\"&gt;Blood Rose&lt;/a&gt; to be drained of their &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt;. Liene managed to escape, though was wounded, both physically and mentally, and by the time the hero(es) found her she was fading. She told them what had happened, and they told her to stay put and wait for reinforcements, while they pressed on ahead to slay the Blood Rose.\nAkara eventually made it to Liene, but by that time, either Liene was dead, or would succumb to her wounds by the time the hero(es) returned from slaying the Blood Rose. Akara declared that Liene's death would not be in vain.\nIn-game.\nLiene is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in the Dark Wood &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;line in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". She is found in the &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Grove\"&gt;Cursed Grove&lt;/a&gt; during the \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Horadric%20Bestiary\"&gt;The Horadric Bestiary&lt;/a&gt;\" quest. She will engage the Fallen with her &lt;a href=\"bows\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt;, but does minimal damage. She is later encountered during the \"&lt;a href=\"Blood%20Resurrection\"&gt;Blood Resurrection&lt;/a&gt;\" quest."}
{"id": "40554", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40554", "title": "Lieutenant Clyfton", "text": "Lieutenant Clyfton was a soldier of &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, stationed at &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt; when it was &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;besieged&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt;. He stayed at his post, even as all his men died around him. When &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; arrived, Clyfton, much to his chagrin, single-handedly raised a catapult, while The Nephalem fended off attacking &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s. With that done, he asked The Nephalem if they could not tell &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Haile\"&gt;Captain Haile&lt;/a&gt; that he'd shouted at them, as he'd promised him that he'd watch his temper.\nIn-game.\nClyfton is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; encountered in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He is encountered at the end of the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Turning%20the%20Tide\"&gt;Turning the Tide&lt;/a&gt;,\" where he raises the third and final catapult."}
