{"id": "2869", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2869", "title": "Life Tap", "text": "Life Tap is a skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThis skill allows the Necromancer to literally suck the life from their victims. The &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; is able to reach into the wellspring of mortality and siphon off its essence, consuming it to replace his own. There is a danger, however, in using the spell too often.\nSynergies.\nUsage.\nThis ability curses a group of enemies so that when attacked, their attacker gains 50% of the &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; damage dealt as life. It's essentially like using a 50% &lt;a href=\"Life%20Leech\"&gt;Life Leech&lt;/a&gt; weapon, but for everybody in the party. The potency of healing does not scale with the skill level.\nLife Tap allows players and creatures to be able to leech life from otherwise leech-immune enemies, such as &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s. Since Life Tap still requires that physical damage be dealt, however, enemies that are &lt;a href=\"immune\"&gt;immune&lt;/a&gt; to said damage are also effectively immune to the curse, despite the graphic appearing over them.\nThis ability is very useful in helping to keep summons alive, and it's a powerful aid to melee allies that lack life leech. While &lt;a href=\"Mercenaries\"&gt;Mercenaries&lt;/a&gt; also benefit, they can receive equipment with sufficient life steal that &lt;a href=\"Amplify%20Damage\"&gt;Amplify Damage&lt;/a&gt; is better for them. This does diminish Life Tap's usefulness to a degree, although useful in its own right.\nAttacks of minions do not replenish the Necromancer's own Life. Normal Life Leech stacks with Life Tap.\nItems.\nSeveral items grant Life Tap skill:\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 9\nHeals for 50% damage dealt"}
