{"id": "6955", "revid": "26096179", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6955", "title": "Lightforge (Great Helm)", "text": "The Lightforge &lt;a href=\"Helms\"&gt;Helm&lt;/a&gt; is a hacked item and will never appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\" or \"\".\nThe item graphic is present on the game CD, but it is unused and its name and the stats are partially derived from a &lt;a href=\"Mace%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt; of the same name: Lightforge and partially invented. Despite popular belief, it is not a deactivated item or a secret item; it is not in the game at all, other than as a hacked item players created and duped widely. \nThere is no telling how this one got started, but it became quite common in the hacks-and-cheats-infested Diablo I &lt;a href=\"Battle.net\"&gt;Battle.net&lt;/a&gt;, and many players with these would swear they were legitimate, and that &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; (or some other powerful monster) dropped it. This is lie and entirely false in terms of gameplay. "}
{"id": "7986", "revid": "26096179", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7986", "title": "Lightforge (Mace)", "text": "The Lightforge &lt;a href=\"Mace%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt; was actually supposed to be given as a quest reward by &lt;a href=\"Tremain%20the%20Priest\"&gt;Tremain the Priest&lt;/a&gt; after the quest &lt;a href=\"Archbishop%20Lazarus%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Archbishop Lazarus&lt;/a&gt; which was originally given by him has been completed. This &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; Mace was never really implemented into the game with exception for that it is only obtainable in Single Player and even then only if a &lt;a href=\"Crackrust\"&gt;Crackrust&lt;/a&gt; is dropped first, however it will most likely morph into another item after one has created a new game and be gone.\nBecause of the good bonuses this item gives, it was commonly hacked. One of the most duped items in the game was the &lt;a href=\"Helms\"&gt;Helm&lt;/a&gt; whose name and stats were taken from this Mace and it was hacked into the game data, it cannot be legally obtained."}
