{"id": "4256", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4256", "title": "Lightning Enchanted", "text": "General Information.\nLightning Enchanted is a monster affix on certain powerful monsters in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". This, as the name implies, gives them affinity with lightning, empowering normal attacks to deal Lightning damage. This also gives them a dangerous backlash upon suffering a hit; &lt;a href=\"Charged%20Bolt%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Charged Bolt&lt;/a&gt; are dispersed, in attempts to damage the hero more than the damage they themselves have caused.\nDiablo II/Lord of Destruction.\nLightning Enchanted grants the following bonuses to the &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monster\"&gt;Unique monster&lt;/a&gt;:\nIn addition, in &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;, minions gain 33% to 50% &lt;a href=\"Resistances\"&gt;Resistance&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Damage\"&gt;Lightning Damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe last bonus is extremely deadly. Firstly, the charged bolts can deal a tremendous amount of damage to a player per bolt. Secondly, if positioned poorly, the player is going to be hit by multiple bolts more often than not. This can be a surefire way to kill off a hero, and is one of the reasons why stacking Lightning resistance could be considered a priority. Melee heroes should fight these monsters with the highest damaging weaponry available. This results in less hits needed, which does help minimize the amount of charged bolts they release. Heroes using ranged weaponry and/or skills are allowed a larger window of opportunity to move out of the way, preventing an overdose of lightning damage. Another surefire way to help reduce damage is through&lt;a href=\"%20Absorption\"&gt; Absorption&lt;/a&gt;\nThe &lt;a href=\"Scarab%20Demon\"&gt;Scarab Demon&lt;/a&gt;s naturally have this bonus. All &lt;a href=\"Sand%20Leaper\"&gt;Sand Leapers&lt;/a&gt; can't have this bonus.\nSuperunique Monsters spawn lightning enchanted and with a conviction aura are probably the most dangerous non-boss enemies in the game, being capable of killing a player in seconds due to reduced lightning resistance and multiple bolts.\nDiablo III.\nLightning Enchanted returns in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" as &lt;a href=\"Electrified\"&gt;Electrified&lt;/a&gt;. It is different from Lightning Enchanted in the following ways:"}
{"id": "38520", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38520", "title": "Lightning Flux", "text": " is the 's ultimate ability for in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThe ability empowers Fists of Thunder by allowing the Monk to &lt;a href=\"teleport\"&gt;teleport&lt;/a&gt; to new targets. Generates a thunderstorm whenever an enemy is defeated."}
{"id": "4228", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4228", "title": "Lightning Fury", "text": "Lightning Fury is an &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Possibly the most devastating, and certainly the most spectacular, of all the techniques learned by an Amazon warrior is Lightning Fury. The High Priestess of Zerae will teach select Amazons the secret of focusing the power of the goddess, consecrating a javelin to become the ultimate weapon of vengeance. The energy contained within the javelin is so powerful that its electrical energy explodes from its stricken target, releasing bolts of lightning that strike down hapless foes nearby. Swift and powerful is the justice administered by an eminent Amazon. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nLightning Fury is thrown as a single projectile, and subsequently releases a set number of lightning bolts towards each of the surrounding monsters when a monster or solid object is hit with this spell. The maximum number of bolts increases with skill level. The minimum number of bolts is determined by the amount of monsters in close proximity to the one being targeted.\nLightning Fury applies only to thrown &lt;a href=\"javelins\"&gt;javelins&lt;/a&gt;, so equipping a &lt;a href=\"Spears\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; will not allow casting this spell.\nIf the javelin goes through the initial target (possible through investment into the &lt;a href=\"Pierce\"&gt;Pierce&lt;/a&gt; Skill and/or obtaining other sources of pierce, such as the &lt;a href=\"Razortail\"&gt;Razortail&lt;/a&gt; unique belt or &lt;a href=\"Wisdom%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Wisdom Rune Word&lt;/a&gt;) then the javelin releases bolts again upon hitting the next hard surface(s).\nThis skill is excellent for crowd control due to its power and accuracy, although it is lacking when confronted with single, more powerful enemies. It is a staple ranged attack of most &lt;a href=\"Javazon\"&gt;Javazon&lt;/a&gt; builds."}
{"id": "6824", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6824", "title": "Lightning Globe", "text": "The Lightning Globe skill is a monster skill that appears in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDiablo II.\nLightning Globe is the signature move of the &lt;a href=\"Tainted\"&gt;Tainted&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Demons\"&gt;Demons&lt;/a&gt;. It can seriously hurt if the player is low on &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Resistance\"&gt;Lightning Resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nMechanics.\nThe Tainted have, along with their powerful melee attack, a ranged lightning attack. This can be particularly devastating when a unique Tainted monster appears with his minions in difficulty. \nBeing a purely elemental attack, and that too of &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, which has a very large damage range, it is a medium ranged ability that takes time to fire. \nThey typically do not start casting the Lightning Globe until they have been injured.\nDiablo Immortal.\n appears in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" as one of the of elite monsters. When used by bosses various spheres of lightning are summoned to move about the arena. &lt;a href=\"Brinegasp\"&gt;Brinegasp&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Akinees\"&gt;Akinees&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Iphael\"&gt;Iphael&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Saarodan\"&gt;Saarodan&lt;/a&gt; also use this skill."}
