{"id": "27337", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27337", "title": "Vampiric", "text": ""}
{"id": "48599", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48599", "title": "Vampiric Powers", "text": "Vampiric Powers were a gameplay mechanic in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", exclusive to \"&lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20the%20Malignant\"&gt;Season of the Malignant&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nVampiric powers are a forbidden art. However, they were utilized by as a necessary evil to defeat Lord &lt;a href=\"Zir\"&gt;Zir&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nVampiric Powers were fueled by &lt;a href=\"Potent%20Blood\"&gt;Potent Blood&lt;/a&gt;. Acquired from fallen adversaries, Potent Blood could be spent in the Vampiric Powers tab within the character menu to unlock a random power or power upgrade. Vampiric Powers could also be unlocked by completing the seasonal questline and from the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Harvest\"&gt;Blood Harvest&lt;/a&gt; event.\nAfter learning a Vampiric Power, players could spend Potent Blood in the powers tab to take its might to the next level. Each power could be upgraded to a maximum of Level 3, and up to five powers could be equipped on a character at a time. When hovering over a Vampiric Power on the tab, it displayed anywhere between 1-3 symbols and numbers. These were called Pacts and the number was their associated cost.\nThere were three Pact types in total\u2014Ferocity, Divinity, and Eternity. Various types of armor had Pact values associated with them. Once a player had both Pact Armor and Vampiric Powers equipped, they would need to ensure that the armor they're wearing provided Pacts that matched the activation cost listed on the power. Standalone Pacts were used to add a specific type of Pact to an item of choice (this could only be done if the maximum amount of that Pact type wasn't already on that item). Cleansing Acids were used to remove Pacts from an item. These crafting items could be pried from the clutches of &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Seekers\"&gt;Blood Seekers&lt;/a&gt;, as well as acquired from the Blood Harvest, &lt;a href=\"Season%20Journey\"&gt;Season Journey&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Opulent%20Coffin\"&gt;Opulent Coffin&lt;/a&gt;s, and through the season's questline. \nList of Powers.\nThere were 22 Vampiric Powers available, able to be used by each &lt;a href=\"class\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Curse\"&gt;Vampiric Curse&lt;/a&gt; ability existed in conjunction with at least some of them. \nDevelopment.\nSix Vampiric Powers will be brought back as &lt;a href=\"aspect\"&gt;aspect&lt;/a&gt;s in the base game."}
{"id": "48845", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48845", "title": "Vampiric powers", "text": ""}
{"id": "36668", "revid": "84037", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36668", "title": "Vane", "text": "Vane was a member of &lt;a href=\"Clan%20Skeld\"&gt;Clan Skeld&lt;/a&gt; and the father of &lt;a href=\"Azgar\"&gt;Azgar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Grey\"&gt;Grey&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nIn his youth, Vane was trained in the ways of the &lt;a href=\"warrior\"&gt;warrior&lt;/a&gt; by his father. In time, he passed on those skills to his elder son, Azgar. He was quite proud of his son, and was open to the idea that Azgar might someday become the champion of Clan Skeld. However, those dreams were shattered when Azgar unintentionally transformed into a &lt;a href=\"Werebear\"&gt;Werebear&lt;/a&gt; and went on a rampage, attacking Grey. The shock reverted Azgar back to his &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; form, and Vane found Azgar cradling Grey's body in their tent. Azgar fled in shame. Vane led a party after him, but could never find his son."}
{"id": "52961", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52961", "title": "Vanguard", "text": "Vanguard is a co-op gameplay mode for \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It was introduced as part of the &lt;a href=\"Crucible%20of%20Justice\"&gt;Crucible of Justice&lt;/a&gt; update.\nGameplay.\nVanguard is a co-op activity where players cull foes in parties of 4 across various objective-based runs. The objective the party is tasked with depends on the event's difficulty tier. In total there are 5 objectives, some of which only unlock in higher difficulty tiers. Objectives may be tasks like escorting an artifact, felling a &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;, or halting a &lt;a href=\"Shardborne\"&gt;Shardborne&lt;/a&gt; invasion.\nTo gain access to the mode, players must be at least at I difficulty, and head to the basement in &lt;a href=\"Cain%27s%20Workshop\"&gt;Cain's Workshop&lt;/a&gt;. A Vanguard portal is available within. Select it, then either bring a 4-person party or engage in matchmaking.\nWhile playing in the mode, players can earn &lt;a href=\"Vanguard%20Charms\"&gt;Vanguard Charms&lt;/a&gt;. Only 5 victories after reset (every Monday and Thursday) will drop a Vanguard Charm as well as enhanced rewards, including chances for special &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary Items&lt;/a&gt;, as well as &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;Set Items&lt;/a&gt;. These rewards can be manually disabled on the Vanguard screen to avoid wasting them on lower-level runs. Regular rewards such as equipment and &lt;a href=\"Beguiling%20Dust\"&gt;Beguiling Dust&lt;/a&gt; are still obtained even without the limited rewards being active.\nHealing potions are not available in the event. However other methods that provide survivability still work, such as the trigger effect of the full set of &lt;a href=\"Vithu%27s%20Urges\"&gt;Vithu's Urges&lt;/a&gt;, as well as skills that provide shields or immunity (such as &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Armor%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Bone Armor&lt;/a&gt;).\nVanguard Skills.\nVanguard skills can be divided into the following:\nLevels.\nThere are 4 levels, with higher levels increasing enemy stats but also the rewards. Levels also have effects depending on the season, such as whether there is a boss at the end or not.\nElite levels are a version of level 4, where monster HP can be further increased by to 130%, 160%, 190%, 250%, 310%, 370%, 460%, 550%, 640% or 750% (10 levels in total). Parties are ranked on the Vanguard leader board by the highest Elite level cleared, and within each level, the fastest clear time.\nHistory.\nIn the update on , Set Items were added to the limited rewards.\nSeason 1 lasted between September 12 and December 5, 2024. It took place in &lt;a href=\"Lidwinter%20Woods\"&gt;Lidwinter Woods&lt;/a&gt;. The Helliquary bosses during this season were &lt;a href=\"Lassal\"&gt;Lassal&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Yamnaal\"&gt;Yamnaal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Iscea\"&gt;Iscea&lt;/a&gt;.\nSeason 1 lasted between December 5, 2024 and February 27, 2025. It took place in &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Ravine\"&gt;Ashen Ravine&lt;/a&gt;. The Helliquary bosses during this season were &lt;a href=\"Gorgothra\"&gt;Gorgothra&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vitaath\"&gt;Vitaath&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gishtur\"&gt;Gishtur&lt;/a&gt; &amp; &lt;a href=\"Beledwe\"&gt;Beledwe&lt;/a&gt;. The Elite levels were introduced in this season.\nAround the update, Vanguard Charms were changed such that instead of manually equipping them, you can choose one on the entry screen and it will be equipped for the duration of the raid."}
{"id": "53011", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53011", "title": "Vanguard Charms", "text": "Vanguard Charms are a type of &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are earned and utilized in the &lt;a href=\"Vanguard\"&gt;Vanguard&lt;/a&gt; co-op mode.\nGameplay.\nVanguard &lt;a href=\"Charm%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Charms&lt;/a&gt; provide new skills to players. Alternatively, they can be used to upgrade other charms, up to a maximum of Level 20. Upgrading these skills initially increases the number of affixes on the skill, and eventually improves the quality and potency of those given affixes.\nWhen salvaging an already upgraded charm, the upgrade materials are returned in addition to the salvage value of the charm minus 5 per upgrade.\nVanguard Charms can also be broken down into Shards, which can then be used to upgrade any Vanguard Charm. Note that Vanguard Charms only function within Vanguard."}
{"id": "53034", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53034", "title": "Vanguard Raid", "text": " is an optional quest in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", released with the \"&lt;a href=\"Crucible%20of%20Justice\"&gt;Crucible of Justice&lt;/a&gt;\" update. It acts as the official prelude to the &lt;a href=\"Vanguard\"&gt;Vanguard&lt;/a&gt; gameplay."}
{"id": "44219", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44219", "title": "Vani", "text": "Vani was a resident of &lt;a href=\"Nevesk\"&gt;Nevesk&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nVani lived in Nevesk. A &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt; priest helped her give birth.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, while attending a service at the Nevesk chapel, Lilith appeared, seducing Vani and the other villagers into following her. While the priest urged them to resist Lilith, Vani took a Cathedral emblem and bashed him in the head. The priest pleaded to her, reminding Vani that he'd helped deliver her child. However, Vani and the townsfolk continued to assault the priest as Lilith left. They placed the headless body in &lt;a href=\"Icehowl%20Ruins\"&gt;Icehowl Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, where &lt;a href=\"Iosef\"&gt;Iosef&lt;/a&gt; later found it. Upon his arrival into Nevesk, Vani and the townsfolk druged Iosef, before Vani and &lt;a href=\"Oswen\"&gt;Oswen&lt;/a&gt; locked him in a shed. \nIosef rambled like a madman about &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s and bit Oswen's hand. &lt;a href=\"The%20Wanderer%20%28Diablo%20IV%29\"&gt;The Wanderer&lt;/a&gt; overheared the interaction when entering the village and investigated. Vani lied to the Wanderer, saying that Iosef had come to the village as a madman, yelling about what he had seen inside the ruins. \nShe asked the Wanderer to investigate the ruins. The Wanderer succeeded, to Vani's apparent surprise. She posed a celebration with the other villagers in order to drug the Wanderer. Oswen wheeled the Wanderer away for a sacrificial ritual, but was killed by Iosef, who saved the Wanderer. Afterwards, Vani and the other townsfolk attacked, but they were killed.\nIn-game.\nVani is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". She is found in &lt;a href=\"Nevesk\"&gt;Nevesk&lt;/a&gt;. She is first introduced inside a shack with &lt;a href=\"Oswen\"&gt;Oswen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Iosef\"&gt;Iosef&lt;/a&gt; as part of the \"&lt;a href=\"Dusk%20on%20the%20Mountain\"&gt;Dusk on the Mountain&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;. She later becomes a &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; and is able to be killed. As a monster, she uses a &lt;a href=\"bows\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt;. "}
