{"id": "45188", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45188", "title": "Varanid", "text": "s are reptilian ambush predators native to the plains near &lt;a href=\"Ivgorod\"&gt;Ivgorod&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nVaranids lunge from the brush, unhinging their jaws wide enough to crush a grown adult \u2014 bones, clothes and all. Yet varanids are nearly always lone hunters, contributing to a belief that they are cannibalistic, and hunt &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s for sport, not nourishment.\nThe fleshy tissue of varanids contain tiny bile-green scales.\nIn-game.\nVaranids are &lt;a href=\"animal\"&gt;animal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They can be found at the &lt;a href=\"Foggy%20Plains\"&gt;Foggy Plains&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nThe common varanid comes in two forms; a green horned one and a white hornless one. This might be due to gender dimorphism."}
{"id": "44071", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44071", "title": "Varanid Yowler", "text": "Varanid Yowlers are &lt;a href=\"animal\"&gt;animal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"monsters\"&gt;monsters&lt;/a&gt; encountered on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Predators, they launch high frequency sonic attacks by vibrating their frills."}
