{"id": "41927", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41927", "title": "Vataos", "text": "The overlord Vataos built a desert gang through imperial cruelty \u2014 raiding travelers, taxing cases, and establishing brutal labor camps throughout &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar&lt;/a&gt;. Vataos first used the &lt;a href=\"Sand%20Scorpions\"&gt;Sand Scorpions&lt;/a&gt; to enrich himself, but after his &lt;a href=\"Tabri\"&gt;anointed successor&lt;/a&gt; deserted, he found a new aspiration: to rebuild &lt;a href=\"Fahiran%20Empire\"&gt;Fahir's kingdom&lt;/a&gt; of death in his own image. \nBiography.\nVataos was a cruel figure, leading through fear and intimidation. Those who refuse to follow his orders were killed.\nOver the years, Vataos had a reign of terror against &lt;a href=\"Shassar\"&gt;Shassar&lt;/a&gt;'s scattered people. In &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; searched for the &lt;a href=\"Scepter%20of%20Fahir\"&gt;Scepter of Fahir&lt;/a&gt;. Vataos dispatched his forces to take them from the outsiders, desiring the scepter for himself. Vataos led the Scorpions himself in an attack on &lt;a href=\"Sereth%20Outpost\"&gt;Sereth Outpost&lt;/a&gt;, where he and &lt;a href=\"Tabri\"&gt;Tabri&lt;/a&gt; met in single combat. She was able to wound him, but disappearing in a puff of smoke, Vataos escaped before she could deliver the killing blow.\nThe Scepter of Fahir ended up in Tabri's hands, which made Vataos desperate. The Sand Scorpions began searching for a weapon to counter the scepter's power. However, events played in the Scorpions' favor, as when the Amber Blades attacked, they drove them back, forcing the Blades to retreat into the &lt;a href=\"Library%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Library of Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;. Inside, Tabri left the Blades to search for Vataos, and using a &lt;a href=\"terminus\"&gt;terminus&lt;/a&gt;, ended up in a &lt;a href=\"Obliterated%20Realm\"&gt;realm beyond Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. However, Vataos followed her through the portal, engaging her in combat. \nVataos was able to claim the scepter and wound Tabri, but was immediately confronted by the Shard-seeker, who defeated him and took the scepter. However, still alive, he attacked Tabri as she and the Shard-seeker sought to leave. He and Tabri remained locked in deadly embrace as the structure collapsed around them. Back in the Library of Zoltun Kulle, the terminus portal closed, leaving their fates unclear.\nIn-game.\nVataos appears in the \"&lt;a href=\"Fahir%27s%20Legacy\"&gt;Fahir's Legacy&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". He is seen fighting Tabri as part of a scripted event, which the player cannot influence.\nVataos later appears as a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;, concluding the \"&lt;a href=\"Curse%20of%20the%20Scepter\"&gt;Curse of the Scepter&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"elite%20quest\"&gt;elite quest&lt;/a&gt;. He is fought in an arena surrounded by portals, where the player can use them to hop from one side of the arena to the next. These can prove useful in evading his attacks, which are as follows:"}
