{"id": "18847", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18847", "title": "Vault", "text": "Vault\u00a0is\u00a0a Hunting\u00a0\u00a0skill in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nWhen activated, Demon Hunter will tumble to where the mouse cursor is pointing (up to 35 yards away). This will carry the player through enemies, but not through &lt;a href=\"Waller\"&gt;Waller&lt;/a&gt; affix placed walls and not through impassable terrain. Cannot be used while &lt;a href=\"Frozen\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fear\"&gt;Fear&lt;/a&gt;ed or &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt;ned, but will liberate from all forms of &lt;a href=\"Slow\"&gt;Slow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Immobilize\"&gt;Immobilize&lt;/a&gt; effects."}
{"id": "50129", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50129", "title": "Vault (Diablo IV)", "text": "Vaults are a gameplay feature of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", exclusive to \"&lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20the%20Construct\"&gt;Season of the Construct&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nA system of subterranean installations, The vaults were constructed by &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;. The vaults are protected by deadly traps, and guarded by &lt;a href=\"construct\"&gt;construct&lt;/a&gt;s. In his hubris, Kulle abandoned the vaults, and over time, a number of &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s lost their lives in their attempts to plunder the vaults.\nWith Kulle's absence, the vaults were left abandoned. This left them free to be corrupted by the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Malphas\"&gt;Malphas&lt;/a&gt;, who took the vaults' power for himself.\nGameplay.\nVaults are a type of . They are filled with elaborate traps, and they include a mechanic where, if the player avoids taking damage from the traps as they complete the vault, the player will receive bonus loot at the end. The main boss of a vault is an unmoving construct which will require the player to fight it while dodging traps in the area.\nVaults can be accessed through &lt;a href=\"Gatehall\"&gt;Gatehall&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "29401", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29401", "title": "Vault Peon", "text": "Vault Peons\u00a0are lesser servants of &lt;a href=\"Greed\"&gt;Greed&lt;/a&gt;, found in &lt;a href=\"The%20Vault\"&gt;The Vault&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". While larger and stronger &lt;a href=\"Vault%20Sentry\"&gt;Vault Sentries&lt;/a&gt; guard the Vaults, and agile and quick &lt;a href=\"Treasure%20Goblin\"&gt;Treasure Goblin&lt;/a&gt;s travel to other worlds to bring treasures, Peons are apparently performing daily duties, such as cleaning, sorting the loot, and construction.\nIn-game.\nVault Peons fight (and are animated) exactly like s, except for they generally do not flee from battle. They attack in large numbers, but pose no threat to &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;, as their &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; and damage are minimal. However, they can serve as a cannon fodder for Sentries, giving those time to get into close combat while players are busy dispatching the horde of Peons."}
