{"id": "27808", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27808", "title": "Vault Sentry", "text": "Vault Sentries (a.k.a. Treasure Realm Sentries or\u00a0Hobgoblins)\u00a0are massive bulky creatures (resembling &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Trooper\"&gt;Demon Trooper&lt;/a&gt;s) guarding the &lt;a href=\"Treasure%20Realm\"&gt;Treasure Realm&lt;/a&gt;. They protect the &lt;a href=\"Treasure%20Goblin\"&gt;Treasure Goblin&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0and &lt;a href=\"Vault%20Peon\"&gt;Vault Peon&lt;/a&gt;s.\nIn-game.\nSentries are usually found in large packs across the Treasure Realm, although usually not a lot per run (for the dungeon itself is very short). They attack with their maces in close combat. Occasionally, they will leap out of the portals, ambushing the player."}
