{"id": "53082", "revid": "46404728", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53082", "title": "Vault of Light", "text": "The Vault of Light is a structure located in both &lt;a href=\"Nahantu\"&gt;Nahantu&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Realm\"&gt;Spirit Realm&lt;/a&gt;, created by the Dedicants of &lt;a href=\"Akarat\"&gt;Akarat&lt;/a&gt; in Akarat's design. The Vault of Light is a bastion that stands in both the Spirit Realm and &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; simultaneously, and it offers protection and peace to those who seek the Light as it is a place of safety from all evil. It is said that Akarat's tomb is located here.\nTomb of Akarat.\nAfter Akarat sacrificed himself during a battle with &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;, his body was carried out of the jungle by &lt;a href=\"Ysevete\"&gt;Ysevete&lt;/a&gt;. Ysevete decided Akarat should be buried within the Vault of Light so his body would be safe from desecration, and she and the other Dedicants brought his body into the Spirit Realm and completed the Vault of Light around his tomb. &lt;a href=\"Istabela\"&gt;Istabela&lt;/a&gt; protected the tomb with wards and spells, and the tomb has remained out of reach of corruption and decay.\nBy &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Crusaders\"&gt;Crusaders&lt;/a&gt; had spent the previous decades searching for Akarat's tomb in the swamps of &lt;a href=\"Hawezar\"&gt;Hawezar&lt;/a&gt;, but had made no progress."}
