{"id": "52122", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52122", "title": "Vendors", "text": "Vendors are noncombat &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; followers in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They can be contracted by players to offer various services in safe zones only. A &lt;a href=\"Vendor%20Contract\"&gt;Vendor Contract&lt;/a&gt; has a duration of sixty days, during which the player can summon a contracted vendor to themselves whenever they are in a safe zone.\nA contracted vendor bears the player's name before their name. When summoned, they follow their contractor for a little over a minute, during which the contractor can request their services to the player's required specifications. Other players can also request services from an idle vendor, but lack the ability to specify. The full picture of a vendor is permanently unlocked in the &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20Gallery\"&gt;Phantom Gallery&lt;/a&gt; after the first time the vendor is contracted."}
{"id": "53967", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53967", "title": "Venerated Closeness", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". When equipped, it enables the player to use a variant of &lt;a href=\"Tendrils%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Tendrils of Blood&lt;/a&gt;. \nHistory.\nIn the update, the damage was increased by 30%, the maximum charges were increased by 1, and the stun duration was increased to 2 seconds."}
