{"id": "29088", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29088", "title": "Vengeful Wind", "text": "The Vengeful Wind is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fist%20Weapons\"&gt;fist weapon&lt;/a&gt; for the in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 70 to drop, and originally only dropped during the &lt;a href=\"Season\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt; One for Seasonal characters. After the end of the Season One, it drops for normal characters as well.\nThe unique affix effectively quadruples the maximum damage per second of the &lt;a href=\"Sweeping%20Wind\"&gt;Sweeping Wind&lt;/a&gt;, although the 'on maximum stack' effects of its runes will also trigger on thirteen stacks instead of three. This is most effective with the &lt;a href=\"Monkey%20King%27s%20Garb\"&gt;Monkey King's Garb&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"set\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn patch 2.4.1 this item was bugged: while its &lt;a href=\"Kanai%27s%20Cube\"&gt;Kanai's Cube&lt;/a&gt; extracted affix grants 7 additional stacks of Sweeping Wind, the item itself only granted 3, as in older versions of the game.\nOriginally this bonus belonged to &lt;a href=\"Alabaster%20Gloves\"&gt;Alabaster Gloves&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "27957", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27957", "title": "Venimite", "text": "Venimite, Tiny and Deadly is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spider\"&gt;Spider&lt;/a&gt;ling that can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Caverns%20of%20Araneae\"&gt;Caverns of Araneae&lt;/a&gt;.\n However, it is the rarest of all Spider monsters in that zone.\nIn combat, it has Fast and Electrified es, and its movement and attack speed are much faster than those of other spiderlings, even taking the Fast affix in account."}
{"id": "4879", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4879", "title": "Venom", "text": "Venom is an &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Poison use is another technique an Assassin has to help even the odds when battling demons and their ilk. An Assassin who has mastered this skill secretly coats her weapons with vile toxins. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nVenom caps the poisoning duration at 0.4 seconds, thus preventing long term poisoning. Consequently, \"all\" other items will only inflict poison damage for 0.4 seconds. Example: Though 700 damage over 10 seconds might seem impressive, only 28 damage will be inflicted due to the 0.4 seconds cap.\nIf a character who is buffed with Venom uses a physical skill that also inflicts poison (&lt;a href=\"Poison%20Dagger\"&gt;Poison Dagger&lt;/a&gt; for example), the duration is instead set to 0.4 seconds plus the duration of the skill itself, while the rate of damage is added to the attack. This results in a monstrous amount of damage added to the skill. For example, if a necromancer with level 15 Venom from &lt;a href=\"Treachery%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Treachery Rune Word&lt;/a&gt; active uses level 25 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Dagger\"&gt;Poison Dagger&lt;/a&gt; (which poisons over 11.6 seconds), the duration of the poison will be set to 12 seconds (11.6 + 0.4), and Venom will provide a total of 9150-9750 damage over that period (305/0.4*12 to 325/0.4*12).\nVenom \"does\" stack with &lt;a href=\"Burst%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Burst of Speed&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Fade\"&gt;Fade&lt;/a&gt; (in earlier versions of the game, it was erroneously overriding Fade if cast).\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 12\nPoison Damage is dealt over 0.4 seconds"}
