{"id": "42672", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42672", "title": "Verathiel", "text": "Verathiel is an &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt; NPC in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\nAfter her birth, Verathiel pledged herself in &lt;a href=\"Auriel\"&gt;Auriel&lt;/a&gt;' service, imbuing herself with the &lt;a href=\"archangel\"&gt;archangel&lt;/a&gt;'s virtue. She was one of the attendants of the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Pandemonium%20Fortress\"&gt;Pandemonium Fortress&lt;/a&gt;. Verathiel would sing of creation to the Worldstone, and with it, worlds and life were born of the dreams of the &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;High Heavens&lt;/a&gt;.\nVerathiel despaired when the Worldstone was stolen on her watch. To atone for her shame, she brought steel and death to the enemies of heaven. When the heavens discovered &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, Verathiel asked her mistress for them to invade Sanctuary and retrieve the Worldstone, but Auriel refused, as she wanted peace.\nUtterly relentless, Verathiel was the leader of a group of angel sentinels. They discovered the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt; as it was taking shape. Cut off from the &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;High Heavens&lt;/a&gt;, they carved out &lt;a href=\"the%20Last%20Vestige\"&gt;a foothold&lt;/a&gt; in the realm, battling &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s over the eons.\nEventually, her cadre was overwhelmed and she was imprisoned by the &lt;a href=\"Baron%20of%20Pestilence\"&gt;Baron of Pestilence&lt;/a&gt; for an unknown amount of time. In &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; encountered her and freed her with the help of &lt;a href=\"Yl%27nira\"&gt;Yl'nira&lt;/a&gt; after killing the Baron. With the help of the dagger, she was able to cleanse the area and turn it to &lt;a href=\"The%20Last%20Vestige\"&gt;a foothold&lt;/a&gt;.\nWith the Shard-seeker's aid, she was able to free two &lt;a href=\"Andalon\"&gt;other&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mikayel\"&gt;angels&lt;/a&gt;. Unfortunately, the &lt;a href=\"Shaddox\"&gt;third one&lt;/a&gt; was already corrupted and had to be killed. She then learnt that &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt; was extracting the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Heaven\"&gt;Heaven&lt;/a&gt; to create demons in &lt;a href=\"Pit%20of%20Anguish\"&gt;pits&lt;/a&gt;. Together with the Shard-seeker they were able to destroy the pits. \nShe was one of the angels that created a &lt;a href=\"portal\"&gt;portal&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Skarn%27s%20Throne\"&gt;Skarn's Throne&lt;/a&gt; for the Shard-seeker to battle him. She then had to rush in to save the Shard-seeker from the resurrected spirit of &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; but the portal, now unstable closed behind her. Unfortunately, Diablo overpowered her, and her &lt;a href=\"Shard%20of%20Verathiel\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; fell into the depths of Hell.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;Two years later&lt;/a&gt;, Verathiel was held captive and tortured by Diablo. He projected an image of her suffering to the Shard-seeker in order to taunt them, and show them the price of defiance.\nThe Unmaking.\nAs Diablo's plans neared completion, he moved his forces (including Verathiel) to the World's Crown. Diablo devised a plan to unmake Sanctuary, and for that, he needed her &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt;. Verathiel still had steadfast faith in the High Heavens even after years of torture so Diablo shifted his efforts to psychological means. He reminded her of the failure of her mistress and the rest of the &lt;a href=\"Angiris%20Council\"&gt;Angiris Council&lt;/a&gt; to rescue her from the Realm of Damnation even twisting the Shard-seeker's actions as abandoning her after they had no more use for her. In the height of her despair he offered her a chance to \"atone\" for her greatest sin; a chance to sing to the Worldstone once again. With that, Verathiel's will broke.\nShe was then moved to &lt;a href=\"Crater%20of%20Unmaking\"&gt;a large crater&lt;/a&gt; and chained to a monolith. The &lt;a href=\"Bride%20of%20Hell\"&gt;Bride of Hell&lt;/a&gt; would occasionally come by to corrupt her angelsong. \nDiablo's ritual for the Unmaking was an imitation of Sanctuary's creation, and required the power of an angel, a demon and creation. He forced Verathiel to sing, with the Worldstone shard and the monolith amplifying her song in potency and range. As each note travelled, it turned all living in its path to ash, and unraveled Sanctuary in its wake. \nVerathiel's Fate.\nDiablo left her after the Unmaking had been set in motion. The Shard-seeker (who survived the Song of Unmaking because of &lt;a href=\"El%27druin\"&gt;El'druin&lt;/a&gt;'s protection) later arrived at the monolith. Verathiel attacked them, hoping for her anguish to end.\nIn-game.\nVerathiel is the &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; companion for the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt; storyline quests in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Verathiel makes a brief appearance in the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Open%20Revolt\"&gt;Open Revolt&lt;/a&gt;\". She returns in the \"&lt;a href=\"Shattered%20Sanctuary\"&gt;Shattered Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;\" update, where she's the boss of the \"&lt;a href=\"Resounding%20Discord\"&gt;Resounding Discord&lt;/a&gt;\" quest. After defeating her, the player makes a choice to either spare or kill her. If spared, she helps the player fight Diablo before he brings her under his thrall again, forcing the player to kill her.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", the &lt;a href=\"Shard%20of%20Verathiel\"&gt;Shard of Verathiel&lt;/a&gt; is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt;.\nCombat.\nWhen helping the player fight Diablo, Verathiel attacks with holy bolts and rains of light.\nWhen acting as an enemy, Verathiel uses the following attacks "}
