{"id": "6450", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6450", "title": "Verdungo's Hearty Cord", "text": "Verdungo's Hearty Cord is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mithril%20Coil\"&gt;Mithril Coil&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt gives the largest boost to &lt;a href=\"Vitality\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"life\"&gt;life&lt;/a&gt; out of all belts, and is therefore useful for any class. This, in conjunction with the rare damage reduction % mod, makes Verdungo's Hearty Cord the best belt for survivability. The only thing to keep in consideration when wearing this belt is that the Life gain earned from its Vitality bonus is \"not\" affected by effects that offer a % increase to the hero's max Life - such as a 's &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Orders\"&gt;Battle Orders&lt;/a&gt;, or a &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Shape%20Shifting%20Skills\"&gt;shape shifting&lt;/a&gt; form.\nStats.\nDefense: 125-158\nRequired Level: 63\nRequired Strength: 106\nDurability: 16\n16 Potion Boxes "}
