{"id": "18946", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18946", "title": "Verrall", "text": "Verrall, Priest of &lt;a href=\"Wortham\"&gt;Wortham&lt;/a&gt;, is a non-player character in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". \nBiography.\nVerrall was sent to Wortham by the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; church. He assumed that the village would be simple and untroubled, and in this, he found his hopes rewarded. However, things changed with the coming of the &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Fallen Star&lt;/a&gt;.\nNot long after the star's fall, a fisherman retrieved a strange artifact in his nets. It looked like a hilt of an &lt;a href=\"El%27druin\"&gt;ancient blade&lt;/a&gt;, but Verrall knew (correctly) that it had to be more. The fisherman argued with him, but Verrall convinced him to leave it in the &lt;a href=\"Wortham%20Chapel\"&gt;Wortham Chapel&lt;/a&gt;, and had &lt;a href=\"Virgil\"&gt;Virgil&lt;/a&gt; guard it.\nUnfortunately, the &lt;a href=\"Coven\"&gt;Coven&lt;/a&gt; were in pursuit of the sword fragment, and attacked Wortham, setting it ablaze. Salvation arrived with &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;, who asked about the fragment. Verrall told the hero(es) that the fragment was in the chapel, and that he would be glad to be rid of it.\nIn-game.\nVerrall appears in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He features briefly in \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Doom%20in%20Wortham\"&gt;The Doom in Wortham&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;."}
