{"id": "42424", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42424", "title": "Vessels", "text": "Vessels are a type of item in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Hunt%20for%20the%20Three\"&gt;Hunt for the Three&lt;/a&gt;, the founding &lt;a href=\"Horadric\"&gt;Horadric&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;s imbued their strengths into these vessels, to be used by future generations of Horadrim. The Horadrim understood their mortality, and sought a way to preserve their knowledge and power for the benefit of future Horadrim. Through a ritual, they instilled a portion of their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; into these gemstones. However, with the fall of the Order, the vessels were scattered across &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. \nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; were tasked by the &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Memory of Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt; to bring the vessels to his &lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;progenitor's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sanctum%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;sanctum&lt;/a&gt;, in order to inherit the legacy of the Horadrim. As the vessels were returned, Horadric memories were activated, who were willing to aid those who proved themselves worthy.\nGameplay.\nVessels are part of the &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20the%20Horadrim\"&gt;Legacy of the Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; gameplay system. The player can obtain vessels through various activities in the game. Once they bring them to the Legacy Shrine in the Sanctum of Iben Fahd, they can gain bonuses. The vessels can be further upgraded through &lt;a href=\"Culling%20Stone\"&gt;Culling Stone&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "43385", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43385", "title": "Vestige Guardian", "text": "The Vestige Guardian is an angel &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\nThe Vestige Guardian was part of a group of angel sentinels led by &lt;a href=\"Verathiel\"&gt;Verathiel&lt;/a&gt;. They discovered the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt; as it was taking shape. Cut off from the &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;High Heavens&lt;/a&gt;, they carved out a &lt;a href=\"the%20Last%20Vestige\"&gt;foothold&lt;/a&gt; in the realm, battling &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s over the eons.\nLocally Sourced.\nThe Vestige Guardian was one of the angels guarding the entrances to the Last Vestige. He stood vigil at the northern entrance.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt; sometime after &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt;'s defeat, a horde of demons attacked the northern entrance. He warned nearby adventurers to seek refuge in the Last Vestige and fought the horde with the help of some &lt;a href=\"Class%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero(es)&lt;/a&gt;. After the horde was defeated, he fell victim to a sneak attack by a &lt;a href=\"Hellhound\"&gt;Hellhound&lt;/a&gt; and fell to the depths below. It is unknown if he survived..\nAfter the attack, &lt;a href=\"Idahir\"&gt;Idahir&lt;/a&gt; built a gate to protect the northern entrance and &lt;a href=\"Zepydra\"&gt;Zepydra&lt;/a&gt; built a ward around the eastern entrance.\nIn-game.\nThe Vestige Guardian appears in the &lt;a href=\"side%20quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Locally%20Sourced\"&gt;Locally Sourced&lt;/a&gt;\" of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHis name is never mentioned in the game. \"Vestige Guardian\" is just a description of his occupation."}
