{"id": "46609", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46609", "title": "Vian", "text": "Vian is a villager that lived in one of the villages in &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nAt a point the well in Vian's village ran dry. He left in search of a new water source. The only other well in the area was controlled by the &lt;a href=\"Sand%20Scorpions\"&gt;Sand Scorpions&lt;/a&gt;, who charged the villagers 100 &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; coins for a drink.\nHe found a pool in the &lt;a href=\"Oasis%20of%20No%20Return\"&gt;Oasis of No Return&lt;/a&gt;; behind the &lt;a href=\"Chamber%20of%20Truth\"&gt;Chamber of Truth&lt;/a&gt;, but the water was contaminated. In his desperation he begged a passing &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; for a little water to drink. After abating his thirst he explained his situation to them and asked the adventurer for protection while he follows the canal from the rock to find the source of the contamination. The canal flowed from the Chamber of Truth, which had a &lt;a href=\"Thorned%20Hulk\"&gt;Bog Lurker&lt;/a&gt; lairing there. Fortunately, the adventure arrived in time to save him.They discovered that the contamination originated from the spring that fed the canal, in which many &lt;a href=\"Frog%20Demon\"&gt;frogs&lt;/a&gt; had made their home.\nTheir last option was to bargain with the Sand Scorpions at the well for water, but they were refused. After watching a villager die of thirst after being refused water, Vian attacked the Sand Scorpions in anger. With the help of the adventurer, the &lt;a href=\"Sand%20Scorpions\"&gt;Sand Scorpions&lt;/a&gt; were killed. Vian resolved to seek help from the Amber Blades in order to prevent the Sand Scorpions from repossessing the well.\nIn-game.\nVian is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". He introduces the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt;; \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Origin\"&gt;The Origin&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
