{"id": "35273", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35273", "title": "Vidian", "text": "Vidian, Lord of Envy\u00a0was a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0who dwelt in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20the%20Firstborn\"&gt;Temple of the Firstborn&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Cultist\"&gt;his followers&lt;/a&gt;. He was also known as Daivin the Adventurer in his human disguise.\nBiography.\nThe Eternal Conflict.\nVidian was once one of &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Sin%20Lieutenants\"&gt;Sin Lieutenants&lt;/a&gt;. Unlike Azmodan's other lieutenants, Vidian seldom obeyed the commands of his master, though during those times that he did, he had a talent for sowing discord and disorder among the &lt;a href=\"Heavenly%20Host\"&gt;Heavenly Host&lt;/a&gt;, which cost the &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s at least one battle during the course of the &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Conflict\"&gt;Eternal Conflict&lt;/a&gt;.\nBlood of the Nephalem.\nAt some point after &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;'s fall, Vidian took up residence in the Temple of the Firstborn. At some point after the defeat of &lt;a href=\"Malthael\"&gt;Malthael&lt;/a&gt;, Vidian's presence, new or otherwise, became noted, as the &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; learnt of something stirring beneath the &lt;a href=\"Shrouded%20Moors\"&gt;Shrouded Moors&lt;/a&gt;. A newly formed &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Cult\"&gt;Blood Cult&lt;/a&gt; took up residence in the temple, and at Vidian's direction, they twisted the flesh of mortals and bent creatures to their ill will. Their particular prey were the newly emergent &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt;, whose blood and power Vidian and the cult desired for themselves, and who they ensnared at times of vulnerability. Vidian personally led more than one adventurer into the temple's depths to die.\nIn what would be his last attempt at beguilement, Vidian encountered &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; in the Shrouded Moors, to whom he posed as a &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; named \"Daivin the Adventurer.\" He offered to join the hero(es) as they made their way through the moors. After the Nephalem destroyed the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Statue\"&gt;Blood Statue&lt;/a&gt;, Daivin commented that they may have brought bad luck upon themselves.\nUpon entering an &lt;a href=\"The%20Excavation\"&gt;excavation&lt;/a&gt; above the temple, Daivin was imprisoned in a cage of bone by &lt;a href=\"Theodosius%20Jordan\"&gt;Theodosius Jordan&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 one of the cultists who had taken up residence in the temple. The Nephalem slew the cultist, but Daivin was apparently killed and torn apart by the cage. In what was apparently his last moments, Daivin asked the Nephalem to not fail him.\nAt the bottom of the temple, \"Daivin\" appeared to the Nephalem a final time. He taunted his foe(s) before assuming his true form of Vidian, Lord of Envy. He engaged the Nephalem in battle, while summoning fellow demons to his side. As the fight progressed, he mocked the Nephalem's allegiance to &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt;. It came to naught, as Vidian was slain.\nIn-game.\nVidian appears in the &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", where he takes on two forms. His first is as \"Daivin the Adventurer\" - Daivin being an anagram of his true name - who functions as an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"follower\"&gt;follower&lt;/a&gt; until The Excavation, although he does not do much in combat.\nHe later appears as a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; at the end of the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20the%20Firstborn\"&gt;Temple of the Firstborn&lt;/a&gt;, within the Sanctum of Blood area (accessed from Level 2). The fight will occur in a square arena without any objects or obstacles.\nVidian is a greatly empowered &lt;a href=\"Reborn\"&gt;Reborn&lt;/a&gt;:\nAt 25% life Vidian will stand in place and fire red bolts at you. He will also spawn Red Vermins to attack you. Stay back from Vidian and keep killing the Red Vermins to rack up kills. Vidian's red bolt attacks will continue to reset the fuse on your massacare bonus. If you have the &lt;a href=\"Azurewrath%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Azurewrath&lt;/a&gt; equipped or in the Cube, you can just stand still and let the Red vermins kill themselves racking up more kills for your Massacare Bonus. When you are done killing them, run up to Vidian and kill him via the Azurewrath and attacks.\nVidian is also present as &lt;a href=\"Vesalius\"&gt;Vesalius&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Rift%20Guardian\"&gt;Rift Guardian&lt;/a&gt;. In this version, he focuses on damaging abilities rather than &lt;a href=\"minions\"&gt;minions&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "35876", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35876", "title": "Vidian, Lord of Envy", "text": "Vidian, Lord of Envy is a &lt;a href=\"tome\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt; that can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Sanctum%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Sanctum of Blood&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20the%20Firstborn\"&gt;Temple of the Firstborn&lt;/a&gt;. It drops from a &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt; in the chamber soon after fighting and defeating &lt;a href=\"Vidian\"&gt;Vidian&lt;/a&gt;. It was written by &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt reads as follows:\n\"\"Vidian was always an...unusual &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;. I only beheld him once, as he would seldom obey the will of his master, &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt;. But on that occasion, he was only too ready to bring disorder to the &lt;a href=\"Heavenly%20Host\"&gt;angelic host&lt;/a&gt;. When he first appeared, we did not know of his insidious threat, and focused our attacks on his mightier brethren. It did not take long before the &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s themselves were beginning to turn on each other, and question their leaders. By the time we figured out what had happened, the battle was lost, and it was too late.\"\""}
{"id": "16818", "revid": "99965", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16818", "title": "Vidrisi", "text": "Vidrisi supposedly was an inhabitant of &lt;a href=\"Toraja\"&gt;Toraja&lt;/a&gt; during the early years of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. Unlike many of her fellow Torajans, Vidrisi did not follow &lt;a href=\"Uldyssian\"&gt;Uldyssian&lt;/a&gt; in his quest to undo both the &lt;a href=\"Triune\"&gt;Triune&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter the destruction of the Triune temple at Toraja (which left parts of the city in ruin) the cunning angel &lt;a href=\"Inarius\"&gt;Inarius&lt;/a&gt; sent emissaries to Toraja, convincing the townsfolk that the &lt;a href=\"Edyrem\"&gt;Edyrem&lt;/a&gt; were bent on destroying all of &lt;a href=\"Kehjan\"&gt;Kehjan&lt;/a&gt;. Vidrisi joined the makeshift peasant army and attacked the Edyrem, resulting in their deaths."}
