{"id": "39135", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39135", "title": "Vine Creeper (Diablo IV)", "text": "Vine Creeper\u00a0is a Companion skill used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", inspired by the classic Creeper minions.\nIn-game.\nThis skill passively summons a vine that cannot be attacked by enemies and do not block enemy pathing. Every few seconds it will emerge and attack a single foe, placing a &lt;a href=\"Damage%20Over%20Time\"&gt;Damage Over Time&lt;/a&gt; effect on them. This poison does not stack, but can be applied to multiple targets one by one.\nVine shares the Druid's basic offensive stats, including those gained from passive talents. Its attacks have zero &lt;a href=\"Proc%20Coefficient\"&gt;Proc Coefficient&lt;/a&gt;. The poison, while it cannot score &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;Critical Hit&lt;/a&gt;s, increases damage based on the Critical Hit Chance/Damage ratio.\nWhen activated, immediately resolves a one-time attack on the target area, hitting each enemy within it once, placing a stronger poison that stacks with the normal one, and Stunning each target.\nThis skill can be used in any Shapeshifting form, and does not change the Druid's current form.\nTalents and effects that empower skills do apply to the Vine Creeper, both passively and actively."}
