{"id": "51981", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51981", "title": "Voidblood Slag", "text": " is an item in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It can be obtained by defeating &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; demons and salvaging their &lt;a href=\"Demonic%20Remains\"&gt;remains&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Charsi\"&gt;Charsi&lt;/a&gt;. It is used for upgrading the Helliquary."}
{"id": "44399", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44399", "title": "Voidwound", "text": "The Voidwound are a quintet of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s, closely associated with the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Abyss\"&gt;Black Abyss&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe Voidwound are demons of darkness. They seek new darkness, and to bring their darkness to new places.\nHistory.\nAncient History.\nThe Voidwound emerged in their current forms from the Black Abyss. All demons reform from the Abyss in time, oftimes in new forms. The demons who would become the Voidwound however, spent \"primordial ages\" inside the Abyss before emerging, and brought the caul of their rebirth with them.\nThe Voidwound emerged in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; not long after their rebirth from the Abyss. Each of the five demons emerged in a different corner of the land (the &lt;a href=\"Sharval%20Wilds\"&gt;Sharval Wilds&lt;/a&gt;, or perhaps further beyond), on the day of an eclipse. &lt;a href=\"Animal\"&gt;Animal&lt;/a&gt;s fell silent, and the nights grew longer. The &lt;a href=\"Nightgrant\"&gt;Nightgrant&lt;/a&gt; observed them and gave them the name \"Voidwound,\" and learnt what they could of these demons. \nThe Voidwound approached the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Tree\"&gt;Great Tree&lt;/a&gt; in Sharval, where they met with at least two of the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Circles\"&gt;Witch Circles&lt;/a&gt;; the Nightgrant and &lt;a href=\"Untameable%20Wilds\"&gt;Untameable Wilds&lt;/a&gt;. The Voidwound made their offer to the Nightgrant dark blessings to shape Sanctuary to their liking, in return for sacrifices. The Voidwound did not mention peace, only one generation of trade between themselves and these mortals. The two exceptions were &lt;a href=\"Apothrus\"&gt;Apothrus&lt;/a&gt; (who remained silent} and &lt;a href=\"Catarag\"&gt;Catarag&lt;/a&gt;, who alone refused to deal with the &lt;a href=\"Witch\"&gt;Witch&lt;/a&gt;es. He instead roared of its &lt;a href=\"Dhasocth%20Iyadur\"&gt;Dhasocth Iyadur&lt;/a&gt;: a time without light.\nThe possibility of a pact was rendered impossible. Untamable Wilds drove away the Nightgrant, and lured Catarag into their glade. They were able to seal Catarag, but at the cost of seven lives. To deal with the remaining Voidwound, the Untamable Wilds circle enacted a desparate plan. They tricked the Voidwound into possessing them, and held them at bay long enough to travel to the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Sea\"&gt;Forgotten Sea&lt;/a&gt;. The Voidwound were sealed in the &lt;a href=\"Voidwound%20Cage\"&gt;Voidwound Cage&lt;/a&gt;, which was sunk beneath the waves. By the time the ordeal was over, the Untamable Wilds circle had been reduced to only ten members. Nevertheless, the circle remained in vigil over the Voidwound's prison.\nRecent History.\nCenturies later,\u2014around &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt; attacked the Voidwound Cage in order to free its prisoners. They were stymied by &lt;a href=\"Nisza\"&gt;Nisza&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 the current wardkeeper of the Untameable Wilds, but their cage was damaged, causing an explosion that scattered &lt;a href=\"Crimson%20Slag\"&gt;bits of the cage&lt;/a&gt; far and wide. This caused the Voidwound to awake. Dymdrail sent &lt;a href=\"the%20Many\"&gt;the Many&lt;/a&gt; to hunt her, but she received help in the form of &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rayek\"&gt;Rayek&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Commander%20Kaya\"&gt;Commander Kaya&lt;/a&gt;. \nWith their prison damaged, the Voidwound were able to break free, just as Nisza returned with help.\nThey were later defeated by the Shard-seeker and sealed in the &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe Voidwound are &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;es in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced as part of the &lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt; update. The Voidwound Helliquary becomes unlocked by completing the prologue &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Chainbreakers\"&gt;The Chainbreakers&lt;/a&gt;\", which is available at &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 60."}
{"id": "44735", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44735", "title": "Voidwound Cage", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; specific zone seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is accessible only in the &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; quest \"\"&lt;a href=\"The%20Chainbreakers\"&gt;The Chainbreakers&lt;/a&gt;\"\".\nThis zone is an island located to the north of the Gulf of Westmarch, where the &lt;a href=\"Untameable%20Wilds\"&gt;Untameable Wilds&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Circle\"&gt;Circle&lt;/a&gt; sealed the &lt;a href=\"Voidwound\"&gt;Voidwound&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nAfter &lt;a href=\"Catarag%20the%20Strangling%20Sun\"&gt;Catarag&lt;/a&gt; was defeated, the Circle's of Sharval devised a plan to seal the remaining Voidwound. After they succeeded in trapping the Voidwound in their bodies, they travelled to a distant island where the Voidwound would be sealed. There a vessel, which extended to beneath the sea had been prepared. Using the light of the &lt;a href=\"moon\"&gt;moon&lt;/a&gt;, a ward was woven into the vessel to trap the Voidwound for as long as the moon gleams. \nAs the ward was made using moonlight, it weakened with the turn of the moon. So the Circles stand vigil, to maintain the ward when the moon wanes\nThe Chainbreakers.\nSometime after the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Nightmares\"&gt;parting of the mists&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;, the island came under attack by the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt;."}
