{"id": "44847", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44847", "title": "Vulture5", "text": ""}
{"id": "3117", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3117", "title": "Vulture Demon", "text": "Vulture Demons are a type of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; class which first appeared in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;. They frequently &lt;a href=\"fly\"&gt;fly&lt;/a&gt; to evade combat.\nSome Vulture Demons are merely &lt;a href=\"animals\"&gt;animals&lt;/a&gt; under the influence of evil forces, but others are &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demonic creatures&lt;/a&gt;. Most Vulture Demons, however, have poor defensive stats and most can be brought down in one to two hits, depending on the weapon and skill used.\nWhen spotting battles between players and other desert creatures, the scavenger is drawn to feed on the endangered adventurer. If they are flying around when a monster is killed near they immediately land down.\nDifferent types of Vulture Demons are: &lt;a href=\"Carrion%20Bird\"&gt;Carrion Bird&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Scavenger\"&gt;Undead Scavenger&lt;/a&gt;s (Undead), &lt;a href=\"Hell%20Buzzard\"&gt;Hell Buzzard&lt;/a&gt;s (Demon), &lt;a href=\"Winged%20Nightmare\"&gt;Winged Nightmare&lt;/a&gt;s.\n&lt;a href=\"Carrion%20Bird\"&gt;Carrion Bird&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Scavenger\"&gt;Undead Scavenger&lt;/a&gt;s are found in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Secret%20of%20the%20Vizjerei\"&gt;Act II&lt;/a&gt; desert areas. &lt;a href=\"Hell%20Buzzard\"&gt;Hell Buzzard&lt;/a&gt;s are found in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Infernal%20Gate\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt; city areas. The &lt;a href=\"Winged%20Nightmare\"&gt;Winged Nightmare&lt;/a&gt;s are found near or within &lt;a href=\"Fetish\"&gt;Flayer&lt;/a&gt; camps.\nBackground.\nBelieved to be the mutated offspring of the large, native vultures that once inhabited these deserts, vulture demons seek only to kill and consume mortal beings that cross their paths. The giant vultures of old were, for the most part, scavengers who ate only the dead or dying. Now befouled, these creatures circle the desert in search of live prey. Their razor sharp beaks and talons can cause deep wounds, and a group of these demons can quickly bring down a victim. Although impossible to target while &lt;a href=\"Fly\"&gt;in flight&lt;/a&gt;, these vultures must land to attack, and are vulnerable when on the ground."}
{"id": "40270", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40270", "title": "Vulture Demon (Guest)", "text": "These &lt;a href=\"Carrion%20Bird\"&gt;Carrion Birds&lt;/a&gt; (vulture5) are &lt;a href=\"Guest%20Monsters\"&gt;Guests&lt;/a&gt;. They can spawn in: \nThey have a 25% chance to deal &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; damage. Their difference to normal Carrion Birds is: a small &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; resistance instead of a &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; one, a tiny &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; resistance and a smaller &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; immunity than the originals. "}
{"id": "36987", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36987", "title": "Vylnas", "text": "Vylnas was a &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;, specifically one of the &lt;a href=\"Five%20Monks\"&gt;Five Monks&lt;/a&gt; who fought in the &lt;a href=\"War%20of%20Thorns\"&gt;War of Thorns&lt;/a&gt; against &lt;a href=\"Entsteig\"&gt;Entsteig&lt;/a&gt;. He was mortally wounded on the battlefield, and the last of the Five left standing, but refused to give into his injuries. His determination and relentless assault broke Ensteig morale, and turned the tide of the war. This eventually lead to the full withdrawal of Entsteig's forces from the field of battle. Later, his deeds were recorded in different historical archives; including that of &lt;a href=\"Poldamyr%27s%20Chronicle%20of%20the%20War%20of%20Thorns\"&gt;Poldamyr&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Volka\"&gt;Elder Volka&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "48075", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48075", "title": "Vylum", "text": "Vylum was a &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt; who lived in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Pestilence\"&gt;Great Pestilence&lt;/a&gt;. \nBiography.\nWhen Vylum was left to die among the plague-infested &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt;s of &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, he was reborn as a dark pied piper full of malicious intent. He would have been burned alive if not for the intervention of the city's &lt;a href=\"Plague%20Rat\"&gt;Plague Rat&lt;/a&gt;s, and soon, he emerged as their lord."}
{"id": "26158", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26158", "title": "Vyr", "text": "Vyr the Vainglorious\u00a0was a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;-lord. By all accounts, Vyr was a tyrant. However, he took enormous pride in his appearance.\nBiography.\nVyr created the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Obelisk\"&gt;Black Obelisk&lt;/a&gt; to gather the power of the &lt;a href=\"Archon\"&gt;Archon&lt;/a&gt;, a being he claimed existed on a different plane of reality. He is even reputed to have stored this macabre power in &lt;a href=\"Vyr%27s%20Astonishing%20Aura\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; of his own design. While manipulating power summoned from beyond &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, he wielded &lt;a href=\"Vyr%27s%20Grasping%20Gauntlets\"&gt;gloves&lt;/a&gt;. However, he was murdered by his own acolytes, who believed he would bring a curse upon them all, and the Black Obelisk was destroyed.\nMuch later, Vyr's armor was found. His &lt;a href=\"Vyr%27s%20Swaggering%20Stance\"&gt;boots&lt;/a&gt; were the last, thought destroyed along with the obelisk. His history was recorded by scholars such as &lt;a href=\"Abd%20al-Hazir\"&gt;Abd al-Hazir&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Valthek\"&gt;Valthek&lt;/a&gt;.\nPersonality and Traits.\nVyr was gifted and incredibly proud (hence his Vainglorious title), yet progressively paranoid: either as result of his magical experiments or otherwise. He demanded a helm protecting his mind from enemies crafted. In his pride, assured of his superiority, Vyr failed to see the true danger coming: convinced of his absolute control of his acolytes, he did not expect them to backstab their master.\nIn-game.\n&lt;a href=\"Vyr%27s%20Amazing%20Arcana\"&gt;Vyr's Amazing Arcana&lt;/a&gt; set can be found in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", being the level 70 offensive class set for &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;s, assembled to greatly augment their &lt;a href=\"Archon\"&gt;Archon&lt;/a&gt; skill. The &lt;a href=\"Nagelring%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Nagelring&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Unstable%20Scepter\"&gt;Unstable Scepter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fazula%27s%20Improbable%20Chain\"&gt;Fazula's Improbable Chain&lt;/a&gt; descriptions also mention Vyr and his Black Obelisk."}
{"id": "25944", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25944", "title": "Vyr's Amazing Arcana", "text": "Vyr's Amazing Arcana\u00a0is an\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt is the offensive class set of the s for level 70. This set can only drop at\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Torment%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0difficulty.\nWhile technically it can be completed by any class, it is specifically designed for Wizards.\nPieces.\nThe set consists of six pieces, all of them are required to complete the set. None of the pieces are Wizard-specific.\nSet Bonus:\nDamage type for Archon with all runes is selected by the highest skill bonus to &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Damage\"&gt;Elemental Damage&lt;/a&gt;. Combustion rune blast damage type will not change; it always delivers &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. If this set is coupled with &lt;a href=\"Chantodo%27s%20Resolve\"&gt;Chantodo's Resolve&lt;/a&gt;, the damage type of that set's special attacks matches the damage type of Archon. &lt;a href=\"Freezing\"&gt;Freezing&lt;/a&gt; effect from Slow Time rune is applied even if non-&lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; damage is selected.\nThe stack bonuses are multiplicative with other similar modifiers, including the Archon's own protection bonus. These bonuses are retained when out of Archon form if the Wizard wears &lt;a href=\"The%20Swami\"&gt;The Swami&lt;/a&gt;. Even better, the 6-piece damage reduction and empowered damage per stack remain active with The Swami as well.\nThe last bonus grants a stack per damaging hit (damaging tick for channeled Disintegration Waves), one stack per ability, regardless of how many enemies it hits (as long as any damage is done). Remember that number of stacks can grow without limit. With &lt;a href=\"Fazula%27s%20Improbable%20Chain\"&gt;Fazula's Improbable Chain&lt;/a&gt;, up to 50 stacks will be gained from the start.\nDamage reduction from the stacks is multiplicative and synergizes well with the 4-piece bonus, but is actually smaller than it sounds: at 100 stacks, it will only add 15% extra protection. However, since the total number of stacks one can accumulate is theoretically unlimited, it can potentially go all the way to 100%."}
{"id": "26066", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26066", "title": "Vyr's Astonishing Aura", "text": "Vyr's Astonishing Aura\u00a0is a Chest piece of the &lt;a href=\"Vyr%27s%20Amazing%20Arcana\"&gt;Vyr's Amazing Arcana&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt only drops at &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 70, and only at\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Torment%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0difficulty.\nPrior to patch 2.1, it was the only &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;-appropriate chest with guaranteed &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;Critical Hit&lt;/a&gt; chance. However, it did not have guaranteed &lt;a href=\"Socket\"&gt;Socket&lt;/a&gt;s.\nIt is one of the few set items with item graphics in the inventory being different depending on the character's gender (as well as class)."}
