{"id": "4885", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4885", "title": "Wake of Fire", "text": "Wake of Fire is an &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Once erected, this trap releases waves of flame that incinerate any opponents within its path. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nWake of Fire places a trap in a chosen area that shoots waves of fire when triggered. Due to its high speed, good number of shoots and wide coverage, this trap can still be very effective well past Normal. However, due to its relatively low synergies and innate damage, as well as the higher amount of fire immune and resistant monsters in later difficulties, the efficiency of this skill is not as high in the very later stages of Nightmare and most of Hell.\nDue to the relative low damage of the spell, dropping many of these traps at once is helpful for dealing more damage. This ability is also much more effective in dungeons, as the cramped corridors and rooms lets the waves hit many more targets than normal.\nThe waves are not radial, but instead are fired in cone-shaped bursts, like &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;'s cold waves.\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 13\nShoots 5 times"}
{"id": "4888", "revid": "48080954", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4888", "title": "Wake of Inferno", "text": "Wake of Inferno is an &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Once an Assassin throws it to the ground, this trap expels a large spout of fire at any opponent who moves within its range. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nAlthough the synergy description provides invalid \"0.5 Yards per level\" both in D2LoD and D2R up to at least version v2.7, actual increase is 1/3 yard/level, and can be verified by looking at the \"range\" value shown in skill. This is a result of the formula for range being ln34/2 + skill('Wake of Fire Sentry'.blvl) , where par3 = 40, par4 = 0, and the divisor is /3 (units/yard). This gives simply ( 20 + skill('Wake of Fire Sentry'.blvl) ) / 3 yards, i.e. 6.6(6) yards + 1/3 yard per WoF level.\nThis skill is the fire-based cousin of the &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Sentry\"&gt;Lightning Sentry&lt;/a&gt;. It fires the at enemies. It has lower range, but deals higher damage than &lt;a href=\"Wake%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Wake of Fire&lt;/a&gt;. It is useful in very small rooms or in a big crowd, where an enemy can receive the full channeled duration.\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 20\nRange: 6.66 yards (since at least 1 point in WoF is required as prerequisite, you will start with 7 yards actually)\nShoots 10 times"}
