{"id": "39011", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39011", "title": "Walking Arsenal", "text": "Walking Arsenal is an ultimate passive talent in the Warlord (Red) tree. It cannot be taken with &lt;a href=\"Unbridled%20Rage\"&gt;Unbridled Rage&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe tooltip is rather misleading on what the skill actually does. Every time an attack is used that forces the Barbarian to switch to another weapon (or a pair of), for each weapon switched to, the effect of 8% increased damage applies, stacking up to 4 times and refreshing with each application. Any two skills that switch weapons are enough to maintain it at all times, similar to how &lt;a href=\"Tal%20Rasha%27s%20Elements\"&gt;Tal Rasha's Elements&lt;/a&gt; Set Bonus worked in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". In other words, the buff is applied \"per different weapon used\", not \"per each of the 4 total weapons equipped\": the Barbarian does \"not\" need to switch rapidly between all 4 of the Arsenal weapons to maintain the maximum effect.\nThe damage boost is multiplicative to other similar effects."}
