{"id": "51965", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51965", "title": "Telluric Fragments", "text": " is an item in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThere is no connection between this item and &lt;a href=\"Telluric%20Pearl\"&gt;Telluric Pearl&lt;/a&gt;, other than both being related to &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Gems\"&gt;Legendary Gems&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nOriginally, \"Diablo Immortal\" had a much more complicated rune system, the description of which can still be found in outdated game guides. The AST rune was the successor to the ATI rune, while dozens of other types of runes existed that were each required for a distinct Legendary Gem. Those other runes were removed and the costs of the recipes updated accordingly.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20Manifest\"&gt;Nightmare Manifest&lt;/a&gt; update, the word \"rune\" was repurposed to refer to a &lt;a href=\"Rune%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;new system&lt;/a&gt;, therefore retaining the AST rune would have cause confusion. It was changed to Telluric Fragments, with the quantity and usage exactly matching that of the old AST rune. leftover AST runes (including from the story quest) can be exchanged at the &lt;a href=\"Apprentice%20Jeweler\"&gt;Apprentice Jeweler&lt;/a&gt;, by choosing the \"Trade Telluric Fragments\" option, which will have a \"Rare Rune Trade\" with the legacy rune in inventory."}
{"id": "44111", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44111", "title": "Telluric Pearl", "text": " is a type of item in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They can be used to craft 5-star &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Gems\"&gt;Legendary Gems&lt;/a&gt;. \nThere is no connection between this item and &lt;a href=\"Telluric%20Fragments\"&gt;Telluric Fragments&lt;/a&gt;, other than both being related to &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Gems\"&gt;Legendary Gems&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere are currently three ways a player can receive Telluric Pearls:\nGameplay.\nAfter collecting 40 Telluric Pearls for the first time, the player needs to talk to Vic in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; to initiate a quest, then complete an &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Rift\"&gt;Elder Rift&lt;/a&gt;. At the end of the Elder Rift, an additional NPC called Yriah [Gem-Binder] will appear, who will provide access to the Telluric Craft interface. The crafted gem always has a 2/5* rating.\nAfter completing the quest, the &lt;a href=\"Apprentice%20Jeweler\"&gt;Apprentice Jeweler&lt;/a&gt; will have a Telluric Craft option."}
