{"id": "24619", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24619", "title": "Tempest Rush", "text": "Tempest Rush is a Secondary &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nIt is one of the few skills that truly benefit from &lt;a href=\"Hexing%20Pants%20of%20Mr.%20Yan\"&gt;Hexing Pants of Mr. Yan&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nWhile active, the Monk will forcibly move (using this skill does not break any existing &lt;a href=\"Immobilize\"&gt;Immobilize&lt;/a&gt; effects, but renders the Monk immune to them while channeling; cannot be cast if Immobilized), hitting enemies they collide with for 390% damage per tick, roughly 10 yards radius. Damage is done once every 12 frames (5 times each second).\nUnder the Tempest Rush, the Monk may move through enemies freely, but not through obstacles and walls. This skill is especially effective with &lt;a href=\"Momentum\"&gt;Momentum&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "43971", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43971", "title": "Tempest Stone", "text": "The Tempest Stone is a artifact possessed by &lt;a href=\"Trond\"&gt;Trond&lt;/a&gt;, and before him, his father and grandfather. It has the ability to manipulate the wind, and both &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;man&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"beast\"&gt;beast&lt;/a&gt; are drawn to it. While a useful tool in the hands of the wise, in the hands of a fool, it can be a curse. &lt;a href=\"Death\"&gt;Death&lt;/a&gt; had a habit of following in its wake.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, the stone was stolen from Trond by a &lt;a href=\"Tempest%20Stone%20Thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt;, who manipulated the wind to his own ends, slowing down an &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; who engaged in pursuit. However, the thief was devoured by an &lt;a href=\"Enormous%20Rockworm\"&gt;Enormous Rockworm&lt;/a&gt;, who in turn was slain by the adventurer. Shifting through the worm's &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt;, the adventurer retrieved the stone and handed it back to Trond, commenting that death, indeed, followed in the stone's wake."}
{"id": "43973", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43973", "title": "Tempest Stone Thief", "text": "The Tempest Stone Thief was a thief who stole the &lt;a href=\"Tempest%20Stone\"&gt;Tempest Stone&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Trond\"&gt;Trond&lt;/a&gt;. Utilizing the stone's power, he was able to manipulate the wind to his advantage, hindering the &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; chasing him. However, he ran afoul of an &lt;a href=\"Enormous%20Rockworm\"&gt;Enormous Rockworm&lt;/a&gt;, which devoured him.\nIn-game.\nThe Tempest Stone Thief is encountered in the \"&lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20the%20Storm\"&gt;Heart of the Storm&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"side%20quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". During the quest, the player must follow him across the Frozen Tundra. If the player gets more than 17 yards behind, the quest fails. The thief himself is not interacted with."}
{"id": "51692", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51692", "title": "Tempest Trial Dungeon", "text": " is a limited-time event in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" following the launch of the &lt;a href=\"Unending%20Storm\"&gt;Unending Storm&lt;/a&gt; update. It runs from May 23 to June 13, 2024. It serves as an introduction to the &lt;a href=\"Tempest\"&gt;Tempest&lt;/a&gt; class.\nGameplay.\nBefore entering, the player must choose one of the 3 recommended builds for the Tempest. They are then warped into the dungeon, which is the last section of &lt;a href=\"Mad%20King%27s%20Breach\"&gt;Mad King's Breach&lt;/a&gt;. The player's build is replaced with the chosen build, including skills, gear and legendary gems. Most character customization options (e.g. Inventory, Paragon, Familiars, the Skills menu) are locked. The dungeon plays out as the original Mad King's Breach.\nRewards.\nAfter completing the event for the first time, 3 &lt;a href=\"Beguiling%20Dust\"&gt;Beguiling Dust&lt;/a&gt; and a mystery &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary Item&lt;/a&gt; are awarded. The reward is only available once, regardless of the build choice."}
