{"id": "42310", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42310", "title": "Temple Guardian", "text": "Temple Guardians are &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are stronger versions of &lt;a href=\"Temple%20Sentinel\"&gt;Temple Sentinel&lt;/a&gt;s.\nLore.\nForged from steel and stone, the Temple Guardians were created during the era of the &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt;. Wary of their own divided natures, the nephalem built Temple Guardians to be By the 13th century, Temple Guardians continued to patrol the grounds of ever-decaying dwellings, protecting their secrets from trespassers.\nIn-game.\nTemple Guardians can be found inactive in a &lt;a href=\"https%3A//tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SwordPlant\"&gt;sword plant&lt;/a&gt; pose, at the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Namari\"&gt;Temple of Namari&lt;/a&gt;'s library. They only seen active when the charge they are to guard has been breached, or if manually activated.\nAll s are immune to &lt;a href=\"knockback\"&gt;knockback&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Guardians\"&gt;Ancient Guardians&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"cosmetic%20set\"&gt;cosmetic set&lt;/a&gt; is themed after Temple Guardians."}
{"id": "46939", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46939", "title": "Temple Sentinel", "text": "s are golem guardians seen guarding the remnants of important sites of the bygone civilization of &lt;a href=\"Valostre\"&gt;Valostre&lt;/a&gt;, most notably the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Namari\"&gt;Temple of Namari&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\ns are &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They can be found at the antechamber of the Temple of Namari in &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt;. They are classified as &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;.\nTemple Guardians initially appear as kneeling statues (see image). Once the player enters range, they activate, and will engage in melee via their &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;swords&lt;/a&gt;."}
