{"id": "41118", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41118", "title": "Temple of Namari", "text": "The Temple of Namari is located on &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe temple is located on &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt;; southeast from &lt;a href=\"Port%20Justinian\"&gt;Port Justinian&lt;/a&gt;, and towards the center of the island, inside &lt;a href=\"the%20Drowned%20Lagoon\"&gt;the Drowned Lagoon&lt;/a&gt;. The structure has an antechamber and a large interior structure. It has at least one auxiliary entrance that leads to its entrance.\nIt holds the &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;ic weapon &lt;a href=\"Yl%27nira\"&gt;Yl'nira&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nThe , originally known as Citadel Valostre, was a temple city, and likely the capital of the &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt; kingdom &lt;a href=\"Valostre\"&gt;Valostre&lt;/a&gt;. At a point, almost all its inhabitants were sacrificed to the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Sargoth\"&gt;Sargoth&lt;/a&gt;. The Betrayer was sealed by the desperate actions of the priestess in the ruins of the temple, along with his top lieutenants. The &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s of some nephalem were bound to the temple to ensure that the dark summoner and his followers never resurfaced\n, with the Priestess &lt;a href=\"Namari\"&gt;Namari&lt;/a&gt; being Sargoth's warden.\nThree beacons were installed, imbued with &lt;a href=\"preservation%20magic\"&gt;preservation magic&lt;/a&gt;, so that Sargoth would be kept alive. A number of barriers were erected to contain Sargoth's own magic. However, over the aeons, his rage granted him power, and his connection to the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt; stronger. \nAt some point, Namari faced Sargoth in single combat, but was defeated.\nOver the years, various adventurers retrieved/stole relics from the temple, and attempted to sell them at &lt;a href=\"Port%20Justinian\"&gt;Port Justinian&lt;/a&gt;. However, misfortune appeared to follow the relics, and eventually, &lt;a href=\"Talva%20Silvertongue\"&gt;Talva Silvertongue&lt;/a&gt; stopped seeing them pass its gates. One of its three beacons ended up in a &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Village\"&gt;different village&lt;/a&gt;. \nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, the last of the temple's three beacons were stolen, which left Namari powerless to deal with Sargoth, whom she warned would escape in time. She was met by &lt;a href=\"Jin\"&gt;Jin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; who agreed to retrieve the beacons in exchange for Namari granting them the items they sought. The first beacon came into the hands of &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Owen\"&gt;Elder Owen&lt;/a&gt;, which kept him alive even as &lt;a href=\"Corpse%20Worm\"&gt;Corpse Worm&lt;/a&gt;s devoured him from the inside. Owen was put out of his misery and the beacon claimed. The second ended up in the hands of the &lt;a href=\"Fetish\"&gt;Fetish&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Rikari%20Village\"&gt;Rikari Village&lt;/a&gt;, and wielded by Chieftain &lt;a href=\"Ongori\"&gt;Ongori&lt;/a&gt;. He was slain by the hero(es) and the beacon retrieved. The third beacon was obtained by &lt;a href=\"Rhodri%20the%20Red\"&gt;Rhodri the Red&lt;/a&gt;, who too was slain. The heroes returned to the temple with the beacons, to Namari's joy. She ordered Jin to stay at the altar lest Sargoth break the seal before they were ready, while she led the other hero(es) into the temple to confront Sargoth. They succeeded in striking him down.\nAfter that, there was a resurgence of adventures raiding the temple for its relics, though they risked acquiring cursed relics.\nGameplay.\nThe temple is encountered as a Bilefen zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", and also serves as a &lt;a href=\"dungeon%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe dungeon becomes accessible during \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Final%20Summoning\"&gt;The Final Summoning&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;. The dungeon itself is divided into a number of chambers. Each chamber has a number of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s the player must kill to progress. When facing &lt;a href=\"Sargoth\"&gt;Sargoth&lt;/a&gt; himself, a number of monsters are spawned in the encounter. These monsters are randomized."}
{"id": "48565", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48565", "title": "Temple of the Deathspeaker", "text": "The Temple of the Deathspeaker was a sunken temple located off the east coast of &lt;a href=\"Hawezar\"&gt;Hawezar&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nIt is unclear who first constructed the temple. However, it was appropriated by &lt;a href=\"Linarian\"&gt;Linarian&lt;/a&gt; in the early history of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. He spent years contemplating the mysteries of life and &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt; within the temple's stifling quiet.\nThe temple became known to the &lt;a href=\"Priests%20of%20Rathma\"&gt;Priests of Rathma&lt;/a&gt;. In order to become the order's &lt;a href=\"Deathspeaker\"&gt;Deathspeaker&lt;/a&gt;, the aspiring &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; had to travel into the temple and face deadly trials in order to determine their worth. Its halls are filled with the &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt;s of those who failed.\nIn-game.\nThe temple is explored in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "34840", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34840", "title": "Temple of the Firstborn", "text": "The Temple of the Firstborn is an ancient structure in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;; the original base of power of &lt;a href=\"Inarius\"&gt;Inarius&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt;. It is found upon the &lt;a href=\"Shrouded%20Moors\"&gt;Shrouded Moors&lt;/a&gt;. where it has escaped the notice of most mortals.\nLore.\nA fortress-temple, the Temple of the Firstborn incorporates architectural designs of both &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s. Its intricate spires rise with angelic grace and precision, reaching up to the stars. Its foundations were \"clawed and dug with demonic hunger down to the roots of the world.\" A significant portion of the temple is located deep underground.\nIt has a main gate, along with numerous courtyards and chambers.\nHistory.\nThe Temple of the Firstborn is one of the oldest locations in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. It is the place where &lt;a href=\"Inarius\"&gt;Inarius&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt; first stepped foot on the world, and was also where they created the first &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt;. The temple was created as a monument to the first of their kind. It served as the base of power for Inarius, Lilith, and their council.\nCenturies after &lt;a href=\"the%20Purge\"&gt;the Purge&lt;/a&gt;, the temple had fallen into ruin.\nIn time, &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;ity itself emerged from this place. \nAt some point, the temple was visited/inhabited by a group of monks.\nDuring/after the &lt;a href=\"End%20of%20Days\"&gt;End of Days&lt;/a&gt;, a new and dangerous cult arose and took residence within the buried structure. Disappearances on the outskirts of the Shrouded Moors began inciting fear, and the dusty tiles of the temple became streaked with disturbingly fresh &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt;. Under the direction of the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Vidian\"&gt;Vidian&lt;/a&gt;, the cultists twisted the flesh of mortals and began bending creatures to their ill will. Abominations filled with hate and driven by bloodlust began stalking the temple's halls. Disappearances on the outskirts of the Moors began inciting fear, and word reached the &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; that a new evil had begun stirring in the area.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; was lured to the temple by Vidian, who appeared before the champion as a human adventurer. However, the Nephalem successfully slew the demon in the temple's depths.\nIn-game.\nThe Temple of the Firstborn is a zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", available in &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt;. It was implemented in Patch 2.6.0.\nThe area features lots of new monsters. The temple itself is infested with demonic enemies, while the grounds above are full of corrupted wildlife.\nNumerous lore moments feature in the dungeon, described as a \"history lesson\" of the setting's pre-history.\nThe Temple consists of two levels: large, vast Level 1, often containing &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monster\"&gt;Unique Monster&lt;/a&gt;s and s, and much smaller, almost empty Level 2. \nLevel 1 can be accessed via &lt;a href=\"waypoint\"&gt;waypoint&lt;/a&gt; or through &lt;a href=\"The%20Sacred%20Path\"&gt;The Sacred Path&lt;/a&gt; from Shrouded Moors.\nLevel 2 can only be accessed by completing &lt;a href=\"The%20Hematic%20Key\"&gt;The Hematic Key&lt;/a&gt; event.\nIn the end of Level 2, there is a passage to &lt;a href=\"Sanctum%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Sanctum of Blood&lt;/a&gt;, where Vidian himself resides."}
