{"id": "54324", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54324", "title": "Tenets of Akarat", "text": "The Tenets of Akarat are a gameplay feature of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced in \"&lt;a href=\"Vessel%20of%20Hatred\"&gt;Vessel of Hatred&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nThe Tenets are scattered throughout &lt;a href=\"Nahantu\"&gt;Nahantu&lt;/a&gt; and are similar in function to the &lt;a href=\"Altars%20of%20Lilith\"&gt;Altars of Lilith&lt;/a&gt;. 30 tenets are located throughout Nahantu, and each tenet grants the player 10 Nahantu &lt;a href=\"renown\"&gt;renown&lt;/a&gt;. Each tenet has a correspondent puzzle that must be solved to unlock it. \nDevelopment.\nThe Tenets replace the Altars of Lilith in that players were frustrated with the latter giving stat bonuses. As such, the Tenets only grant renown."}
