{"id": "1665", "revid": "13298744", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1665", "title": "Terror's End (Quest)", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20End\"&gt;Terror's End&lt;/a&gt; is the third and last quest of &lt;a href=\"The%20Harrowing\"&gt;Act IV&lt;/a&gt;. It is initiated by talking to &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt; after &lt;a href=\"Hell%27s%20Forge%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Hell's Forge (quest)&lt;/a&gt; has been completed. Tyrael tasks the player with destroying the main antagonist of the game, namely &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; himself.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; is defeated, the quest is completed. Of the original \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" game, this was the final quest. However, for players who bought the expansion, the adventure doesn't end here: when they speak to &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt;, he will tell them about the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; and Baal's army that is marching towards it. He would then open a portal to the city of &lt;a href=\"Harrogath\"&gt;Harrogath&lt;/a&gt;.\nFurther Information and Tips.\nSee the &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; article for tips on how to defeat Diablo in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". In the original game, the game would be exited automatically slightly less than a minute and a half after Diablo's defeat, leaving little time to collect loot and for chatting with the denizens of the &lt;a href=\"Pandemonium%20Fortress\"&gt;Pandemonium Fortress&lt;/a&gt;.\nWithout the expansion, Tyrael only tells the player that \"for now you should rejoice,\" without mentioning Baal."}
