{"id": "24289", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24289", "title": "Terror Bat", "text": "Terror Bats\u00a0(a.k.a. Shrieking Terrors) are &lt;a href=\"Beast\"&gt;Beast&lt;/a&gt; creatures found in the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Marsh\"&gt;Blood Marsh&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and &lt;a href=\"Paths%20of%20the%20Drowned\"&gt;Paths of the Drowned&lt;/a&gt; in in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nTerror Bats are larger than the &lt;a href=\"Vile%20Bat\"&gt;Vile Bat&lt;/a&gt;s, and may attack from a distance with piercing sonic waves. When needed, they can pick up nearby\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Boggit\"&gt;Boggit&lt;/a&gt;s, bite them, and turn them into &lt;a href=\"Bogan%20Brute\"&gt;Bogan Brute&lt;/a&gt;s. The process can go the other way as well. In addition, Terror Bats may perform a 'gliding charge', dashing forward and damaging and briefly &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt;ning all enemies in their path.\nShrieking Terrors appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are featured in &lt;a href=\"Defense%20of%20Cyrangar\"&gt;Defense of Cyrangar&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Onslaught%20%28event%29\"&gt;Onslaught&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Path%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Path of Blood&lt;/a&gt; events."}
{"id": "26039", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26039", "title": "Terror Demon", "text": "Terror Demons\u00a0are &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; enemies in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nTerror Demons are easily recognized by their sheer size and spiked form shaped after &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;, Lord of Terror. However, they are of very dark color, and appear only at the moment of attack, so looking around for them will not help the player to avoid being ambushed.\ns appear in the \"&lt;a href=\"Splintered%20Souls\"&gt;Splintered Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" update of Diablo Immortal.\nIn Diablo III, s are only encountered in , &lt;a href=\"Pandemonium\"&gt;Pandemonium&lt;/a&gt; dungeons or &lt;a href=\"Nephalem%20Rift\"&gt;Nephalem Rift&lt;/a&gt;s. They are often hiding in shadows, only appearing once the player comes close, leaving glass cannon builds at a severe disadvantage, with no means to prevent the ambush. They only have melee attacks, which are rapid and cause significant Physical damage, but their most notable ability is their curse applied on each damaging hit. This curse reduces all healing received by 25% for 10 seconds (used to be 75% at the time of game release, but proved to be overpowered, possibly the main reason why Act IV was run rarely in the first place).\nSome Terror Demons can also disappear in case of danger, forcing the player to focus on other targets, and then come back to attack from unexpected direction. While invisible, Terror Demons cannot be harmed in any way.\nTerror Demons usually attack in groups of two or more, or with a large retinue of &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Vermin\"&gt;Shadow Vermin&lt;/a&gt;. Be wary of multiple demons emerging from shadows at once, as their attacks can easily kill a hero if applied simultaneously.\nAs of Patch 2.1 (or 2.2), Terror Demons can be found in visible state, and they only rarely if ever use their vanishing ablity anymore."}
{"id": "50883", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50883", "title": "Terror Essence", "text": " is an &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced in the \"&lt;a href=\"Precipice%20of%20Horror\"&gt;Precipice of Horror&lt;/a&gt;\" update.\nLore.\n is a sticky substance found in &lt;a href=\"Terror%20Rift\"&gt;Terror Rift&lt;/a&gt;s. When touched,it shows the person a vision of a nearby &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20Pillar\"&gt;Oblivion Pillar&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nTerror Essence is essential to partaking in &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20Pillar\"&gt;Oblivion Pillar&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Hellslayer%20Bounties\"&gt;Hellslayer Bounties&lt;/a&gt;. Terror Essence can come from rewards chests provided by Stygian Spires, and improves the player's chances of obtaining &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Equipment\"&gt;Eternal Equipment&lt;/a&gt;. Essence can be bought and sold at &lt;a href=\"Wynton%27s%20Grand%20Market\"&gt;Wynton's Grand Market&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"platinum\"&gt;platinum&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere is a Codex task for using 10 Terror Essences in a week that rewards a piece of equipment irrespective of &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Points\"&gt;Battle Points&lt;/a&gt; being capped or not. This task can hold up to 2 weeks' progress.\nSource.\n&lt;a href=\"Terror%20Rift\"&gt;Terror Rift&lt;/a&gt; - when destroying a Stygian Spire, the reward chest has a chance to contain a Terror Essence.\nHistory.\nOriginally, the codex task for using 10 essences in a week reset every Monday. In the update, it was changed to keep up to 2 weeks' progress."}
{"id": "50881", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50881", "title": "Terror Rift", "text": "Terror Rifts are a feature of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced as part of the &lt;a href=\"Precipice%20of%20Horror\"&gt;Precipice of Horror&lt;/a&gt; update.\nLore.\nTerror Rifts are gateways into &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, bursting out of the mortal realm's topsoil. They were used by &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;'s forces in their assault against Sanctuary. &lt;a href=\"Adventurer\"&gt;Adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s were forced to venture through the rifts to halt the incoming invaders.\ns need an &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20Pillar\"&gt;Oblivion Pillar&lt;/a&gt; at a particular location to act as a beacon for them to open.\nGameplay.\nTerror Rifts will be active all the time. 1 zone will be invaded at random, with one Terror Rift portal appearing in the zone. The zone rotates every hour. The zone with the active Terror Rift portal is denoted on the world map, as well as the next zone with a countdown timer. Players must track down the portal to enter. After entering, each player gets 13 minutes to complete the Rift, with Stygian Spires spawning at set times. Even if the Terror Rift entrance closes at the hour, players who are already inside can stay for the remainder of their 13 minute periods.\nThe rift will take players to the Terrorwrought Realm version of the zone where the rift appeared. This map matches the geography of the normal map but the &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s are replaced with Terrorwrought monsters. These monsters drop Stygian Fragments, with Elite monsters dropping more fragments. After gathering a certain number of Fragments from fallen foes (displayed via a progress bar), the player must search for a Stygian Spire. The number of fragments required is 100, 150, 250 and 300 respectively for the four Spires. Sacrificing the required Fragments in one of these pointed beacons will initiate a one-on-one fight with a &lt;a href=\"Rift%20Guardian\"&gt;beefier opponent&lt;/a&gt;. Toppling this enemy grants a reward chest. The player can complete this process as many times as they can within 13 minutes, in order to press onto more plentiful rewards. Rewards may be earned up to 10 times a week from the Terror Rifts, resetting each Monday at 3 a.m. server time. Once a player acquires all weekly rewards, they can continue to run Rifts but will only be able to earn drops from enemies. Different players will see Spires in different locations on the map.\nA successful run, whether solo or with a group of up to four others, will be met with a chance to earn &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Equipment\"&gt;Eternal Equipment&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Terror%20Essence\"&gt;Terror Essence&lt;/a&gt; and other rewards from each reward chest the player(s) receive. Terror Rifts can be played starting at Difficulty I, with the quality of rewards received scaling with the difficulty level. If the first 3 spires destroyed don't drop a Terror Essence, the 4th one is guaranteed to drop one.\nDevelopment.\nUpon release, monster kills could not be shared between players, even between party members. The first player to tag a monster got the drop. This was later fixed with an update.\nOriginally there was no guarantee on the Terror Essence drop. The guarantee was added in the &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20Manifest\"&gt;Nightmare Manifest&lt;/a&gt; update.\nIn the July 24 2024 update, the Terror Rift icons on the World Map were changed to be greyed out if the rift is not currently active (i.e. until 3 minutes before opening time).\nIn the update, Terror Rifts were changed in several ways:"}
