{"id": "44362", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44362", "title": "Terror Zealot", "text": "Terror Zealots are members of the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt;. They often reach a point of devotion where they produce &lt;a href=\"congealed%20terror\"&gt;congealed terror&lt;/a&gt; from their tear glands.\nIn-game.\nTerror Zealots appear as &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" in &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt;. They encircle the player."}
{"id": "44091", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44091", "title": "Terror Zone", "text": "Terror Zones are a gameplay feature of \"\".\nOverview.\nTerror Zones are opt-in. When playing a Terror Zone-enabled game, every hour, the armies of the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt; will focus their demonic might on specific zones, terrorizing them. The monsters in these zones will be at least two levels higher than the player's current level or their original level, up to a maximum per difficulty. The experience received and the loot dropped by killing a terrorized monster will be based on this new level. In addition, terrorized monsters will also grant additional experience points.\nThe base player level used for the above calculations are taken from the creator of the game. If the host leaves the game, a new player will be selected for the base.\nUpon entering a Terror Zone-enabled game, players will be informed of the current terrorized areas through a message sent to via the Chat Box. When the time for new terrorized zones draws near, players will be informed of the impending changes via the Chat Box.\nIn addition, players will be informed that you\u2019re entering a terrorized area by several indicators:\nIn Hell difficulty, Terror Zones are the only places in which monsters can drop Sundered &lt;a href=\"Charm\"&gt;charms&lt;/a&gt;."}
