{"id": "51944", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51944", "title": "The Angered Dead", "text": "The Angered Dead is an &lt;a href=\"Event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt; that takes place in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20Commons\"&gt;Westmarch Commons&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20V%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". A &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; may be assigned to complete it.\nNear the end of one of the roads winding through the Commons, the Brenden Manor Grounds are marked by stone steps leading up to a circular courtyard and fountain, abutting a house to the west and a stately tomb to the east. A dirt path runs behind the tomb, allowing the courtyard to be bypassed if desired.\nA few Shadow Swordwielders and &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Ghostly Masons&lt;/a&gt; attack from various points in the area upon approach, and Summoned &lt;a href=\"Summoned%20Soldier\"&gt;Soldiers&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summoned%20Shield%20Guard\"&gt;Shield Guards&lt;/a&gt; may be stationed in the courtyard. Upon entering the courtyard, the ghostly &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Darius%20Brenden\"&gt;Lord Darius Brenden&lt;/a&gt; seals the gates and attacks the intruding &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;, assisted by a few other Swordwielders and Masons. Defeating him completes the event, awarding gold and experience."}
{"id": "31604", "revid": "5562046", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31604", "title": "The Angiris Council", "text": "The Angiris Council is a &lt;a href=\"tome\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt; found in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", specifically within the 1st tier of the &lt;a href=\"Gardens%20of%20Hope\"&gt;Gardens of Hope&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt reads as follows:\n\"The &lt;a href=\"Angiris%20Council\"&gt;Angiris Council&lt;/a&gt; is comprised of the five &lt;a href=\"archangel\"&gt;archangel&lt;/a&gt;s who hold dominion over the &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;High Heavens&lt;/a&gt;. They determine the laws by which all angels must abide. Each of them embodies a pure aspect of creation: &lt;a href=\"Imperius\"&gt;valor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;justice&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Auriel\"&gt;hope&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Itherael\"&gt;fate&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Malthael\"&gt;wisdom&lt;/a&gt;. - &lt;a href=\"Selathiel\"&gt;Selathiel&lt;/a&gt;, Angiris Scribe\""}
{"id": "49553", "revid": "27473235", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49553", "title": "The Annulet", "text": " is the council that have led the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Knights\"&gt;Blood Knights&lt;/a&gt; since &lt;a href=\"Fernam\"&gt;Fernam&lt;/a&gt; disappeared. They maintain the lifeblood of their order and work tirelessly to stockpile &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;al artifacts.\nThey also bestow armor to new blood knights, designed after their grievous wounds with aesthetic puncture marks.\nAt some point, they are shown a series of visions from an artifact, depicting the cataclysmic potential of the Worldstone. In &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, if the hero(es) who discovers its first shard in Wortham is a Blood Knight, they would remark it has preoccupied the council enough to let knights loose."}
{"id": "48338", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48338", "title": "The Anointed Ascent", "text": "The Anointed Ascent is a &lt;a href=\"Fractured%20Peaks\"&gt;Fractured Peaks&lt;/a&gt; zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It is located east of the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Judgment\"&gt;Fields of Judgment&lt;/a&gt;, and leads to &lt;a href=\"Alabaster%20Peak\"&gt;Alabaster Peak&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Ascent is explored during the \"&lt;a href=\"Pilgrimage\"&gt;Pilgrimage&lt;/a&gt;.\" An altar is located at the ascent's peak, but unlike prior altars in the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;line, isn't treated as its own sub-zone. The &lt;a href=\"tome\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"To%20the%20Penitent\"&gt;To the Penitent&lt;/a&gt;\" is located here. The &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20the%20Penitent\"&gt;Shrine of the Penitent&lt;/a&gt;, however, is its own sub-zone."}
{"id": "50285", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50285", "title": "The Apothecary's Brother", "text": "The Apothecary's Brother is an &lt;a href=\"Event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Highlands%20Cave\"&gt;Highlands Cave&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; is sometimes offered to complete it.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; must help Rike the Apothecary rescue his brother from &lt;a href=\"Coven\"&gt;Coven&lt;/a&gt; cultists, who have poisoned his brother and left him deep in the cave because they are \"after Rike's elixirs\". Rike follows the hero into the cave, and begins administering an antidote once his brother is found, at which point &lt;a href=\"Brakan\"&gt;Brakan&lt;/a&gt; and a pack of cultists appear through portals and attack. After their defeat, Rike gives thanks and returns to town with his brother.\nObjectives.\nAlthough essentially the entire Highlands Cave must be cleared before finding Rike's brother, it is not large. The event rewards gold and experience.\nDialogue.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Lyndon\"&gt;Lyndon&lt;/a&gt; the Scoundrel is accompanying the Nephalem, he tells Rike \"Don't worry about it. Brothers should keep together.\" When the Nephalem asks, he declines to elaborate.\nRewards changes.\nThe event rewards the usual gold and experience. Rike used to reward players with &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt;, but no longer does so after consumable health potions were removed from the game, despite his dialogue remaining unchanged."}
