{"id": "6806", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6806", "title": "The Atlantean", "text": "The Atlantean is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; from \"\".\nThe Atlantean has good enhanced damage and a great boost to &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Rating\"&gt;Attack Rating&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;. However, other than its enhanced damage, the Atlantean has little other added damage elemental or otherwise, making it a rather dull (but still effective) weapon.\nDue to its skill bonuses, the Atlantean is best off in the hands of a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;. Since it does not give boosts to any specific type of Paladin skill, a variety of Paladin builds can use it with equal effectiveness. Along the same logic, some Paladins more specific in their build may find other weapons more useful.\nCompared to other unique swords, the Atlantean is simple but all-round useful. Still, other unique weapons have properties that are far more useful in terms of damage (such as the &lt;a href=\"Deadly%20Strike\"&gt;Deadly Strike&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Headstriker\"&gt;Headstriker&lt;/a&gt;).\nStats.\nOne-Hand Damage: (54-63) To (129-150)\nRequired Level: 42\nRequired Strength: 127\nRequired Dexterity: 88\nDurability: 144\nSword Class - "}
{"id": "30", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30", "title": "The Awakening", "text": "The Awakening is a &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20series\"&gt;\"Diablo\"&lt;/a&gt;-flavoured RPG for the Advanced Dungeons and Dragons system. Its quests are based on those of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\", but the playable characters are mainly the ones from \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". \nDescription.\nThis action-packed epic takes the world of the DIABLO II computer game and translates it into the ultimate AD&amp;D adventure. You can create AD&amp;D heroes with a DIABLO twist or use heroes from any AD&amp;D campaign, then send them off to challenge terrors once found only on a computer screen. The adventure starts in &lt;a href=\"Tristram\"&gt;Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, the battleground of the original DIABLO game, where &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;, Lord of Terror, rules a legion of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s. There, the heroes explore the mysterious &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral\"&gt;Monastery&lt;/a&gt; - full of dangers and challenges pulled right from DIABLO but enhanced for your tabletop game!\nExternal Links.\n&lt;a href=\"http%3A//www.amazon.com/Diablo-II-Awakening-Advanced-Roleplaying/dp/0786916125/ref%3Dpd_sim_b_2%3Fie%3DUTF8%26amp%3BrefRID%3D14GNC74SQVN9SBBZ1DE3\"&gt;Amazon page&lt;/a&gt;"}
