{"id": "37785", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37785", "title": "The Burning Man", "text": "The Burning Man is an in &lt;a href=\"Act%20V%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Paths%20of%20the%20Drowned\"&gt;Paths of the Drowned&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; is sometimes offered to complete it.\nA square stone-lined pit in the swamp houses a &lt;a href=\"bogan\"&gt;bogan&lt;/a&gt; sacrificial ritual. Steps descend into it from the south corner, and a large number of heavy torches are stuck firmly into the ground in a circular pattern. From above, many &lt;a href=\"Boggit\"&gt;Boggit&lt;/a&gt;s and a few &lt;a href=\"Tusked%20Bogan\"&gt;Tusked Bogan&lt;/a&gt;s can be seen sitting reverently in front of a figure constructed from sticks, but they quickly turn to attack when intruded upon. After they are all slain, the figure animates itself into &lt;a href=\"The%20Wickerman\"&gt;The Wickerman&lt;/a&gt;, who not only attacks directly, but also causes jets of fire to shoot rapidly between the torches throughout the fight. Killing him completes the event, awarding gold and experience.\nThe torches cause walking to be slightly more difficult than usual within the pit: Despite appearing quite skinny, the torches are propped up with a crossing support, causing it to occupy a little extra space in one direction which sometimes blocks movement.\nLocation.\nThe event spawns in a unique square area that is easy to spot on the map.\nThe area for this event is reproduced as the \"Festering Pit\" in a &lt;a href=\"Vision%20of%20Enmity\"&gt;Vision of Enmity&lt;/a&gt;. Luckily, the fire beams associated with The Wickerman fight do not appear."}
