{"id": "26755", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26755", "title": "The Cloak of the Garwulf", "text": "The Cloak of the Garwulf\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Cloaks\"&gt;cloak&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0for the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Demon%20Hunter\"&gt;Demon Hunter&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires\u00a0&lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a050 to drop. In Patch 2.0., it replaced &lt;a href=\"The%20Inquisitor\"&gt;The Inquisitor&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt increases the number of wolves summoned by &lt;a href=\"Companion\"&gt;Wolf Companion&lt;/a&gt; to 3. The affix will not work with other runes, and the damage bonus that the wolves' howls provide do not stack (so you get 15% as usual, not 45%), but the three of them become a considerable force and are effective at locking enemies in close combat, allowing the Demon Hunter to fire at their foes from safety. With the &lt;a href=\"Embodiment%20of%20the%20Marauder\"&gt;Embodiment of the Marauder&lt;/a&gt; set, it will still call two additional wolves, but only wolves (not other companion types).\nPrior to Patch 2.1, it also granted a &lt;a href=\"movement%20speed\"&gt;movement speed&lt;/a&gt; bonus (which cannot normally roll on a chest armor). "}
