{"id": "23072", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23072", "title": "The Compass Rose", "text": "The Compass Rose is a ring piece of the &lt;a href=\"Endless%20Walk\"&gt;Endless Walk&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 60 to drop.\nThis ring has a &lt;a href=\"movement%20speed\"&gt;movement speed&lt;/a&gt; bonus, which cannot normally roll on a ring. It is also one of the few items with 5 Primary affixes. As such, those who desire the most potent of &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;critical hit&lt;/a&gt; stats in addition to access to the &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Gem\"&gt;most potent of gems&lt;/a&gt; may find this to be worthwhile, even if only for a little bit of time."}
{"id": "44788", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44788", "title": "The Comtessa", "text": "The Comtessa was a mysterious individual who arrived in the &lt;a href=\"Big%20House\"&gt;Big House&lt;/a&gt;. Ultimately, her actions were responsible for the emergence of &lt;a href=\"the%20Countess\"&gt;the Countess&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Comtessa was tall for a woman, with dead-black hair that, if unbraided, went all the way to her ankles. She had brown skin like silk, and spoke in a musical tongue. She wore a ruby ring as large as a pigeon\u2019s egg.\nBiography.\n&lt;a href=\"Nan\"&gt;Nan&lt;/a&gt; suspected that the Comtessa and her retinue had a routine; to squat in one place for as long as they dared, then leave before too many questions were asked.\nAutumn Meeting.\nOne autumn night, the Comtessa and her retinue arrived at the Big House in the marshes of northern &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt;. They were apparently unbothered by the cold, and dressed richly for travelers, and as &lt;a href=\"Nan\"&gt;Nan&lt;/a&gt; noted, bereft of horse smells for one who had ridden for so long. The people of the House were enraptured by them. Her retinue addressed her as \u201cComtessa;\u201d supposedly a title in her own tongue. \nThe Comtessa claimed that she and her retinue were travelling through Khanduras on pilgrimage, and hoped to rest at the Big House before continuing onward. She flattered the &lt;a href=\"the%20Countess\"&gt;daughter&lt;/a&gt; of the noble family there, who immediately demanded that rooms be made for the company, and their horses fed and watered. \nThe Comtessa did not emerge until late afternoon. The girl showed her around the grounds, the Countess smiling at everything, but refused to enter the chapel (\u201conce you have seen one backwater Khanduras chancel, you have seen them all\u201d). As the days passed, the Comtessa\u2019s demenor shifted. One moment she was languishing and philosophical, the next, laughing like a maenad. She and her retinue slept late, which they claimed was the fashion. Sometimes, until nearly sundown, they would hunt and bring back game. The retinue sometimes played coarse games, tossing the corpses of their kills to one another, feigning to bite the creatures, and at times, taking raw blood from their kills. Sometimes, the Comtessa went with them.\nThe girl lavished gifts on the Comtessa, who in turn gifted her her ruby ring. In exchange, the girl gave her an even larger ring, which even the Comtessa could not help but admire. Nan noted that the Comtessa looked at her lady with \u201cthe calculating glance of a cat with a very plump mouse.\u201d The Comtessa often made fun of her ignorance, or used her as the butt of a joke, but the girl never noticed, as she was so enraptured.\nAfter a fortnight, the Comtessa declared that she and her retinue would leave, as they intended to reach the mountain pass before the winter snows closed it. The girl declared that the pass was already inhospitable, and that the Comtessa and her people should stay until the thaw. The Comtessa smiled and declared that they would hold a party to celebrate the young lady.\nDepartures.\nExactly what happened in the party was a mystery to all but those who attended (the Comtessa, her retinue, and the young girl who was besotted with her). When the girl retired to her chambers before dawn, she was trembling; her dress was torn, her hair was in disarray, and she was grey-faced. In the morning, the Comtessa and her retinue had departed, along with the girl. Furthermore, a number of servants had gone missing.\nThe girl was eventually brought home, confused but unhurt, save a shallow knife slit at the side of her throat. She could not say if anyone had attacked her. Many of the servants, however, never came back. One bloated corpse of a young man was found when the snow started to thaw, his neck broken open, and an expression of horror on his face.\nLegacy.\nExactly who, or what, the Comtessa was remained a mystery, but her actions were felt long after her departure. The girl, who took to calling herself \u201cCountess,\u201d descended into madness, bathing in the blood of virgins before eventually meeting her end."}
{"id": "44383", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44383", "title": "The Confined", "text": "The Confined are a type of &lt;a href=\"transformed%20%28monster%29\"&gt;Transformed&lt;/a&gt; encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Prison\"&gt;Abandoned Prison&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nTime in a &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gibbeting\"&gt;gibbet cage&lt;/a&gt; is a common punishment for &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt; prisoners without influence. The warping power of the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; fused those thus confined to their cages. With the prison unsealed, they now crawl into the light in search of vicious indemnification. Now, they crawl or roll around, even dropping from the ceiling to attack their foes."}
