{"id": "35052", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35052", "title": "The Cursed Bellows", "text": " \nThe Cursed Bellows is a\u00a0major &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Chest\"&gt;Cursed Chest&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" with a 100-kill bonus objective. It takes place in Level 3 of the &lt;a href=\"Halls%20of%20Agony\"&gt;Halls of Agony&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; may be offered to complete it.\nThe primary enemies are &lt;a href=\"Risen%20Dead\"&gt;Inferno Zombies&lt;/a&gt;. Possibly because of the unique layout and spawning pattern, they tend to spawn in much greater numbers than most other Cursed Chest events.\nUnlike most other Cursed Chests, The Cursed Bellows takes place in a special area in the Halls of Agony which only rarely appears normally. It is a large chamber divided into three lanes, with the center lower than the outer lanes and containing the chest itself. Four parallel vents are built into the floor at medium intervals, crossing all lanes and spraying fire periodically (before, during, and after the event). The zombies crawl out from grates where the vents run under the walls of the center lane.\nObjectives.\nCompleting the event rewards either one or two &lt;a href=\"Chests%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Radiant Chests&lt;/a&gt;, depending on whether or not you completed the bonus objective."}
