{"id": "53464", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53464", "title": "The Cursed Cellar", "text": "The Cursed Cellar is a major &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Chest\"&gt;Cursed Chest&lt;/a&gt; event with a 100-kill bonus objective in &lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Damp%20Cellar\"&gt;Damp Cellar&lt;/a&gt; under the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Tristram%20Road\"&gt;Old Tristram Road&lt;/a&gt;, and is one of very few &lt;a href=\"bounties\"&gt;bounties&lt;/a&gt; that can be offered along the road or in &lt;a href=\"The%20Old%20Ruins\"&gt;The Old Ruins&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe monsters appearing for this event are all &lt;a href=\"Risen\"&gt;Risen&lt;/a&gt;, climbing out of the floor of the cellar at a higher rate than most cursed chests.\nUnlike most other Cursed Chests of this type, this one has a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monster\"&gt;Unique Monster&lt;/a&gt; \"event boss\" of sorts: &lt;a href=\"Farnham%23Diablo%20III\"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the former town drunk of Old Tristram and now a &lt;a href=\"Risen%20Dead\"&gt;Risen Dead&lt;/a&gt;, who appears in the hallway to the cellar towards the end of the event. Killing him is not required to complete the event, but he approaches quickly enough to end up in the fight before time expires."}
