{"id": "26716", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26716", "title": "The Cursed Crystals", "text": "The Cursed Crystals is an &lt;a href=\"event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in &lt;a href=\"Act%20V%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Infested%20Ruins\"&gt;Infested Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, a small dungeon in the &lt;a href=\"Battlefields%20of%20Eternity\"&gt;Battlefields of Eternity&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; may be offered to complete it.\nThe Ruins consist of an initial area with a Cursed Crystal object hovering in the center, a larger oval area with two Cursed Crystals, and a short path connecting them with a &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Chest\"&gt;Cursed Chest&lt;/a&gt; in the middle. The Crystals must be activated one by one, causing several Warscarred &lt;a href=\"Warscarred%20Ravager\"&gt;Ravagers&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Warscarred%20Footsoldier\"&gt;Footsoldiers&lt;/a&gt; to attack the first two times. Destroying the final crystal spawns &lt;a href=\"Keeper%20Hashemel\"&gt;Keeper Hashemel&lt;/a&gt; himself, and even more Ravagers.\nUpon killing the Keeper, the cursed on the chest is lifted and the event is complete.\nThis event is one of the two featuring Cursed Crystal prisons: &lt;a href=\"The%20Crystal%20Prison\"&gt;The Crystal Prison&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Pandemonium%20Fortress\"&gt;Pandemonium Fortress&lt;/a&gt; level 2 features identical devices."}
{"id": "49675", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49675", "title": "The Cursed Eternal Chest", "text": "The Cursed Eternal Chest is a\u00a0marked &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Chest\"&gt;Cursed Chest&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Event\"&gt;Event&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20III%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Woods\"&gt;Eternal Woods&lt;/a&gt; and can be given as a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt;. The only monsters are &lt;a href=\"Hungry%20Corpse\"&gt;Hungry Corpse&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "35051", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35051", "title": "The Cursed Glacier", "text": " \nThe Cursed Glacier is a major &lt;a href=\"Cursed%C2%A0Chest\"&gt;Cursed\u00a0Chest&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Icefall%20Caves\"&gt;Icefall Caves&lt;/a&gt; Level 1, in &lt;a href=\"Act%20III%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". Completing it may be assigned as a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt;.\nWintersbane &lt;a href=\"Lacuni%20Huntress\"&gt;Huntresses&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lacuni%20Stalker\"&gt;Stalkers&lt;/a&gt; are the primary enemies for this event. Unlike most other Cursed Chests, there are pits in the ground surrounding the chest, with some enemies appearing on the other side. Some will leap over the pits to attack, but others may be hard to reach quickly for characters without fast ranged spells, making the bonus objective more difficult.\nObjectives.\nLike other major Cursed Chests, completing the event awards a &lt;a href=\"Radiant%20Chest\"&gt;Radiant Chest&lt;/a&gt;, with a second awarded for accomplishing the bonus objective."}
