{"id": "25559", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25559", "title": "The Cursed Peat", "text": "The Cursed Peat is a major &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Chest\"&gt;Cursed Chest&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Paths%20of%20the%20Drowned\"&gt;Paths of the Drowned&lt;/a&gt;. It appears at the top of the hill that is also used for\u00a0&lt;a href=\"The%20Lord%20of%20the%20Hill\"&gt;The Lord of the Hill&lt;/a&gt;, but both events cannot spawn at the same time.\nWhen the curse is activated, many &lt;a href=\"Boggit\"&gt;Boggit&lt;/a&gt;s and some &lt;a href=\"Tusked%20Bogan\"&gt;Tusked Bogan&lt;/a&gt;s spawn rapidly. Killing 100 of them within the time limit grants a bonus chest. This event has an unusually high spawn rate, making it easier to achieve the bonus objective than with many other Cursed Chests."}
