{"id": "29124", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29124", "title": "The Dagger of Darts", "text": "The Dagger of Darts is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ceremonial%20Knives\"&gt;ceremonial knife&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", added in patch 2.1. It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 12 to drop.\nThe unique affix enhances not only the Witch Doctor's own &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Dart\"&gt;Poison Dart&lt;/a&gt;s, but also those fired by &lt;a href=\"Fetish%20Army\"&gt;Fetishes&lt;/a&gt;, both those of the Head Hunters and those granted by the &lt;a href=\"Carnevil\"&gt;Carnevil&lt;/a&gt;. This works on all Fetishes, even on &lt;a href=\"Sycophants\"&gt;Sycophants&lt;/a&gt; or those summoned by . In result, the darts pierce for the full distance, inflicting damage on every enemy in their path.\nAs of 2.6.5, it also multiplicatively increases damage of Poison Darts."}
{"id": "33094", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33094", "title": "The Dahlgur Oasis", "text": "The Dahlgur Oasis is a &lt;a href=\"Tomes\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt; found in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", inside a Keepsake Box in the &lt;a href=\"Dahlgur%20Oasis\"&gt;Dahlgur Oasis&lt;/a&gt;, usually right next to the small pond east from entrance.\nThis tome is required for the \"Historian of Caldeum\" achievement.\nIt reads as follows:\n\"Three centuries ago, a much smaller &lt;a href=\"Caldeum\"&gt;Caldeum&lt;/a&gt; depended upon small wells for its water. Then came the mysterious &lt;a href=\"Dahlgur\"&gt;Dahlgur&lt;/a&gt;, offering Caldeum an oasis of unparalleled splendor located in an area previously thought to be desert, asking only that his name be permanently affixed to the land. Then, he vanished into the wastes. \u2014 &lt;a href=\"Abd%20al-Hazir\"&gt;Abd al-Hazir&lt;/a&gt; \""}
{"id": "52847", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52847", "title": "The Dark Citadel", "text": "The Dark Citadel is a PvE activity for \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", be released in the \"&lt;a href=\"Vessel%20of%20Hatred\"&gt;Vessel of Hatred&lt;/a&gt;\" expansion.\nLore.\nLocated in &lt;a href=\"Nahantu\"&gt;Nahantu&lt;/a&gt;, the Dark Citadel is located in a crater made during the &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Clan%20Wars\"&gt;Mage Clan Wars&lt;/a&gt;. It is from here that the first &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; were created. While the khazra eventually spread out from the Citadel, a number of khazra remained inside the structure, trying to practice &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;. In comparison to the khazra that spread across &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, these khazra are a throwback to their original forms. They became known as the &lt;a href=\"First%20Khazra\"&gt;First Khazra&lt;/a&gt;, distinguishing themselves from their divergent kin.\nThe First Khazra still remained in the citadel by the Great Enmity. They used the powers located in the citadel and the crater it was located in to perform experiments in a bid to resurrect their dark god, &lt;a href=\"Zagraal\"&gt;Zagraal&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe Dark Citadel offers endgame PvE content for groups of 2-4 players with combat and cooperative puzzles. Players need to split their forces and simultaneously traverse separate paths. Players are able to earn exclusive appearances by completing The Dark Citadel on top of its weekly reward cache. Each wing of the dungeon has a different flavor and different combination of attacks players need to overcome. A number of &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;es feature in the citadel that are designed in accordance with group play.\nWhile inside the citadel, players have access to unique markers/icons that can be slotted into their emote wheel. This can be used to mark points of interest to other players, guide them, etc.\nDevelopment.\nThe traps in the Citadel were iterated from those present in \"&lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20the%20Construct\"&gt;Season of the Construct&lt;/a&gt;\". Comments from developers have implied that the Citadel was created first, with the lore being developed later."}
