{"id": "31902", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31902", "title": "The Demon's Demise", "text": "The Demon's Demise is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Hand%20Crossbows\"&gt;Hand Crossbow&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Hunter\"&gt;Demon Hunter&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", added in patch 2.3.0. It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 70 to drop.\nThis weapon was only available to &lt;a href=\"Season\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt;al characters during Season Four, but once this Season ended, started to drop for normal characters as well.\nThe unique affix, as of 2.4.2, causes &lt;a href=\"Spike%20Trap\"&gt;Spike Trap&lt;/a&gt; to damage any enemy its blast (and only the blast, not secondary arcs of Lightning Rod) has hit again after 1 second, for the same damage, without any other effects that can trigger on a blast. It does not cause the trap to go off twice; the damage is simply duplicated again on each affected enemy, and does not chain further unless a new trap is actually detonated.\nDevelopment.\nPrior to 2.4.2, which changed the functionality of Spike Trap, the unique affix caused &lt;a href=\"Spike%20Trap\"&gt;Spike Trap&lt;/a&gt; (with Sticky Trap rune only) to spread to enemies the explosion hits. The original target wouldn't gain a new application upon detonation. This effect might chain repeatedly, being especially lethal to large hordes of foes."}
