{"id": "49677", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49677", "title": "The Demon Gates", "text": "The Demon Gates is an exploration &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20III%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", found in &lt;a href=\"Arreat%20Crater%20Level%202\"&gt;Arreat Crater Level 2&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe player must destroy 4 Demon Gate objects scattered throughout the middle portion of the map. They look the same as those encountered during the fight against &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt; - large spiked totems hovering over demonic portals in the ground - and both are similar to the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Summoner\"&gt;Demon Summoner&lt;/a&gt;s sometimes found in Arreat Crater in &lt;a href=\"Campaign%20Mode\"&gt;Campaign Mode&lt;/a&gt;. Upon approach, each gate will rapidly emit several orbs of demonic energy which turn into &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Trooper\"&gt;Demon Trooper&lt;/a&gt;s, and several &lt;a href=\"Demonic%20Hellflyer\"&gt;Demonic Hellflyer&lt;/a&gt;s may swoop in as well. This variety of Demon Gate is destroyed by channeling on it without being interrupted. Clearing the spawned monsters is not strictly necessary, but likely the easiest way to complete the bounty quickly.\nWhen the last Demon Gate is destroyed, a &lt;a href=\"Radiant%20Chest\"&gt;Radiant Chest&lt;/a&gt; will appear."}
