{"id": "3127", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3127", "title": "Tir Rune", "text": "A Tir rune is a low &lt;a href=\"Runes\"&gt;rune&lt;/a&gt; which can be &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;ed into equipment in \"\". Some popular rune words use Tir runes, but the value of Tir runes is limited by how frequently they drop. Tir runes are powerful for early game characters especially, as the increased mana on kill is particularly useful for characters with small mana pools. \nEffects.\nSocketing an item with a Tir rune increases the item's level requirement to 13, unless it was already higher.\nSources.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Countess\"&gt;The Countess&lt;/a&gt;'s extra rune drops on any difficulty can include Tir runes.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Hellforge\"&gt;Hellforge&lt;/a&gt; on normal difficulty has a 1 in 11 chance to drop a Tir rune as part of its quest reward.\nThe Act 2 Good treasure class has a chance to drop a Tir rune, as do higher Good treasure classes.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; can transmute three &lt;a href=\"Eld%20Rune\"&gt;Eld runes&lt;/a&gt; into one Tir rune.\nRune Words.\nTir runes are used in these &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Words\"&gt;rune words&lt;/a&gt;:\nRecipes.\nTir runes are used in three &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; recipes."}
