{"id": "6729", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6729", "title": "Titan's Revenge", "text": "Titan's Revenge is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ceremonial%20Javelin\"&gt;Ceremonial Javelin&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUnlike its sister unique javelin, &lt;a href=\"Thunderstroke\"&gt;Thunderstroke&lt;/a&gt;, Titan's Revenge gives more consistent bonuses to all &lt;a href=\"Javelin%20and%20Spear%20Skills\"&gt;Javelin and Spear Skills&lt;/a&gt;, and is ideal for &lt;a href=\"Javazon\"&gt;Javazon&lt;/a&gt;s that specialize in &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Skills\"&gt;Poison Skills&lt;/a&gt; and those specifically using &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Fury\"&gt;Lightning Fury&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn some ways, Titan's Revenge is superior to &lt;a href=\"Thunderstroke\"&gt;Thunderstroke&lt;/a&gt; because it replenishes quantity, increases the player's &lt;a href=\"Movement%20Speed\"&gt;run/walk speed&lt;/a&gt;, and provides a large bonus to &lt;a href=\"dexterity\"&gt;dexterity&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt;. The increased stack size is also very nice because it reduces the number of trips required\u00a0to repair the weapon.\nWhile the 5-9% &lt;a href=\"Life%20Steal\"&gt;Life Stolen Per Hit&lt;/a&gt; is a nice added bonus, it doesn't really amount to much because most of the damage dealt by Javazons is &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Damage%29\"&gt;Lightning Damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nDespite the fact that this weapon is an &lt;a href=\"Exceptional%20Items\"&gt;exceptional&lt;/a&gt; rather than an &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Items\"&gt;elite&lt;/a&gt; unique, Titan's Revenge is generally considered the best unique javelin in the game for player versus monster, especially if upgraded to a &lt;a href=\"Matriarchal%20Javelin\"&gt;Matriarchal Javelin&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Ethereal%20Items\"&gt;Ethereal&lt;/a&gt; versions of this weapon are highly sought after, especially when used in melee.\nStats.\nThrow Damage: (70-79) To (185-212)\nOne-Hand Damage: (70-79) To (137-155)\nRequired Level: 42\nRequired Strength: 25\nRequired Dexterity: 109\nMax Stack: 140\nJavelin Class \u2013 Fast Attack Speed"}
